1
00:00:30,876 --> 00:00:35,914
[EP.3 Your life belongs to you,
and only your choices can be right]

2
00:00:35,914 --> 00:00:39,351
[A night washed in moonlight]

3
00:00:39,351 --> 00:00:41,487
[Lights sparkle all around]

4
00:00:41,487 --> 00:00:44,089
[The night gets a little warmer]

5
00:00:44,089 --> 00:00:45,824
Let's go sit over there where it's warm.

6
00:00:45,824 --> 00:00:47,025
Shouldn't you do that bit?

7
00:00:47,025 --> 00:00:49,728
- Ba-ra-ba-ba-bam.
- Ba-ra-ba-ba-bam.

8
00:00:49,728 --> 00:00:51,163
- It's so warm.
- Ba-ra.

9
00:00:51,163 --> 00:00:52,631
It's nice and warm.

10
00:00:52,631 --> 00:00:56,101
[Time to show the guests their rooms]

11
00:00:56,702 --> 00:00:59,338
[Cheers fill the cozy house]

12
00:00:59,338 --> 00:01:00,939
- Oh, man.
- Gosh, look at the photos!

13
00:01:00,939 --> 00:01:02,875
They put pictures up here.

14
00:01:02,875 --> 00:01:04,877
[Old Guardian props welcome the guests]
Gosh, they had stuff like this?

15
00:01:04,877 --> 00:01:07,245
Oh, Eun Tak!

16
00:01:08,580 --> 00:01:10,549
[Eun Tak from ten years ago]
Oh, man. She's adorable.

17
00:01:10,549 --> 00:01:12,317
She's just so cute.

18
00:01:12,317 --> 00:01:13,685
Make sure you look at everything.

19
00:01:13,685 --> 00:01:15,453
Oh! There's the ring!

20
00:01:16,088 --> 00:01:17,389
You sold that, remember?

21
00:01:17,389 --> 00:01:18,924
- That's the ring I sold.
- Right.

22
00:01:18,924 --> 00:01:21,214
[Sunny's jade ring Samshin sold]
I bought this one.

23
00:01:21,914 --> 00:01:23,662
- No way. They kept this.
- Yeah,

24
00:01:23,662 --> 00:01:27,266
- they actually kept it.
- I can't believe this ring is here.

25
00:01:27,266 --> 00:01:28,867
Did you know they had this?

26
00:01:28,867 --> 00:01:30,602
- Huh?
- A photo essay.

27
00:01:30,602 --> 00:01:33,372
- Huh? No, Dong Wook, I had no idea.
- This is my first time seeing it.

28
00:01:33,372 --> 00:01:35,541
- They made a photo essay?
- Yeah.

29
00:01:35,541 --> 00:01:37,976
Really? Let me take a look.

30
00:01:40,412 --> 00:01:45,017
[Guardian's best scenes and lines
all packed into one photo essay]

31
00:01:45,017 --> 00:01:48,858
[One page, and the memories return]

32
00:01:49,555 --> 00:01:50,556
This has us

33
00:01:50,556 --> 00:01:53,091
- from when we looked our best, right?
- It does.

34
00:01:54,526 --> 00:01:57,538
That's me. That's me!

35
00:01:57,538 --> 00:01:58,764
[That's Eun Tak ten years ago]
Me!

36
00:01:58,764 --> 00:02:00,232
I loved this scene.

37
00:02:00,232 --> 00:02:03,635
You know why?
Go Eun gets all pouty right after this.

38
00:02:03,635 --> 00:02:05,771
And the way she walks off mad is so funny.

39
00:02:05,771 --> 00:02:09,641
They show up and save her
from a kidnapping so dramatically.

40
00:02:09,641 --> 00:02:13,211
But she's mad because they came without a car,
so now she has to walk.

41
00:02:15,113 --> 00:02:16,460
[From Episode 2]

42
00:02:16,460 --> 00:02:19,866
[Grim Reaper and Goblin come to save Eun Tak]

43
00:02:23,422 --> 00:02:26,725
[They pull off a perfect rescue, but...]

44
00:02:26,725 --> 00:02:28,927
You came...

45
00:02:28,927 --> 00:02:31,230
without a car?

46
00:02:31,230 --> 00:02:34,098
We don't really get around by car.

47
00:02:35,033 --> 00:02:37,803
[The endless walk home...]

48
00:02:37,803 --> 00:02:40,873
What kind of road doesn't have
a single car going by?

49
00:02:40,873 --> 00:02:44,510
[Extremely sulky]

50
00:02:44,510 --> 00:02:47,512
That scene was so lovely.

51
00:02:50,215 --> 00:02:52,760
- He looks amazing.
- Gosh, this picture is really something...

52
00:02:52,760 --> 00:02:54,786
- He looks so great.
- This is incredible.

53
00:02:54,786 --> 00:02:56,055
[General Kim Shin looks so striking,
you just have to stare]

54
00:02:56,055 --> 00:02:58,523
He's seriously good-looking.

55
00:02:59,558 --> 00:03:00,993
He looks great.

56
00:03:00,993 --> 00:03:02,094
Huh?

57
00:03:02,094 --> 00:03:03,595
- He's good-looking!
- Right.

58
00:03:03,595 --> 00:03:06,031
[That face is timeless]
They really are all so handsome. Seriously.

59
00:03:06,031 --> 00:03:07,399
[The memories rush right back]
Oh, my!

60
00:03:07,399 --> 00:03:09,101
- The kiss scene flew by, didn't it?
- Yeah.

61
00:03:09,101 --> 00:03:12,404
I really thought Yongpyong might finish me off.

62
00:03:12,404 --> 00:03:14,439
- You could tell that shoot was brutal.
- Right.

63
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:17,109
I swear, I barely made it through that day.

64
00:03:17,109 --> 00:03:23,096
[He reunites with Eun Tak
at the ski resort after she runs away]

65
00:03:24,650 --> 00:03:30,282
[With harsh wind and snow,
they battled the cold nonstop]

66
00:03:33,091 --> 00:03:36,361
[His hands turned red]

67
00:03:36,361 --> 00:03:39,831
That's how freezing it was.
You know this part, when he does this?

68
00:03:39,831 --> 00:03:41,433
After he did that and they called cut,

69
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:45,070
[Even that hair-pat was tough]
this side of his hand would burn from the cold.

70
00:03:45,070 --> 00:03:47,039
- He'd be going, "Ugh..." like that.
- Oh, seriously?

71
00:03:47,039 --> 00:03:49,575
It was that bad. It was unreal.

72
00:03:49,575 --> 00:03:51,577
We were freezing when we filmed that, right?

73
00:03:51,577 --> 00:03:53,145
Yeah, we really were.

74
00:03:53,145 --> 00:03:55,514
I feel like Byung Chul
must've been the coldest.

75
00:03:55,514 --> 00:03:57,349
- A bit, I guess.
- Your costume was really thin too.

76
00:03:57,349 --> 00:03:58,884
But since it was hanbok,

77
00:03:58,884 --> 00:04:01,753
- I could sneak layers underneath.
- Right. Hanbok lets you hide stuff.

78
00:04:01,753 --> 00:04:04,423
The hand with the prosthetic makeup
must've been freezing, right?

79
00:04:04,423 --> 00:04:06,158
- Oh, right. That part...
- Right?

80
00:04:06,158 --> 00:04:09,294
Because it was prosthetic makeup,
if I put it somewhere,

81
00:04:09,294 --> 00:04:11,554
I was scared it'd get messed up,
so I kept it out like this.

82
00:04:11,554 --> 00:04:14,032
- That was all silicone, wasn't it?
- Yes.

83
00:04:14,032 --> 00:04:15,516
- With silicone.
- That's why,

84
00:04:15,516 --> 00:04:18,624
after they put on my old-woman makeup,
I couldn't eat, use the bathroom,

85
00:04:18,624 --> 00:04:20,105
or do anything.

86
00:04:20,105 --> 00:04:22,173
Because your hands were useless.

87
00:04:23,675 --> 00:04:25,243
[So much effort went
into these unforgettable scenes]

88
00:04:25,243 --> 00:04:28,981
How do you never get any older?

89
00:04:28,981 --> 00:04:32,650
I want to see them destroyed.

90
00:04:34,486 --> 00:04:36,254
That ending where you showed up

91
00:04:36,254 --> 00:04:37,793
- with the purple tongue.
- Right.

92
00:04:37,793 --> 00:04:40,692
- That one really shocked people.
- Yeah,

93
00:04:40,692 --> 00:04:42,628
- the episode 11 ending was so creepy that...
- Oh, after the Jaws Bar thing?

94
00:04:42,628 --> 00:04:44,863
- It was just...
- The audience completely freaked out.

95
00:04:44,863 --> 00:04:47,665
[A shocking look still talked about]
Yeah, people went wild.

96
00:04:48,367 --> 00:04:50,702
Can I open this script?
I think it belongs to someone.

97
00:04:50,702 --> 00:04:52,070
There's a name written right here.

98
00:04:52,070 --> 00:04:53,972
- Huh? What's this?
- It's hers.

99
00:04:53,972 --> 00:04:55,707
- Can I look at it?
- Yeah, go ahead.

100
00:04:55,707 --> 00:04:57,376
- For real?
- Is that yours?

101
00:04:57,376 --> 00:04:59,544
Because actors write character notes
and stuff inside their scripts.

102
00:04:59,544 --> 00:05:01,113
You wrote all these...

103
00:05:01,113 --> 00:05:02,881
That's exactly why I want to see it.

104
00:05:02,881 --> 00:05:05,450
[Her notes on becoming Sunny]
My script didn't look anything like this.

105
00:05:05,450 --> 00:05:06,918
Look at the front of episode three.

106
00:05:06,918 --> 00:05:11,456
My character notes are painfully embarrassing.

107
00:05:12,190 --> 00:05:14,726
- "So it doesn't come off fake."
- Hey, don't read that!

108
00:05:14,726 --> 00:05:16,928
- "So it doesn't come off fake."
- Hey, don't read that!

109
00:05:18,096 --> 00:05:19,831
You showed everyone and now you're saying no?

110
00:05:19,831 --> 00:05:20,832
No, you can't!

111
00:05:20,832 --> 00:05:22,434
[Curious one] [Curious two]
"So it doesn't come off fake."

112
00:05:22,434 --> 00:05:25,871
Wait, does that mean some characters
are supposed to seem fake?

113
00:05:25,871 --> 00:05:27,172
You wrote the most obvious note ever.

114
00:05:27,172 --> 00:05:28,473
- No, seriously. Don't.
- Let me see.

115
00:05:28,473 --> 00:05:29,875
- Come on. Let us see it too.
- I'm so embarrassed.

116
00:05:29,875 --> 00:05:31,410
How is your handwriting this pretty?

117
00:05:31,410 --> 00:05:32,878
In Na, I want to see it too.

118
00:05:32,878 --> 00:05:34,946
[Got it]
How is your handwriting so pretty?

119
00:05:35,881 --> 00:05:37,916
[Look at this]
This is adorable.

120
00:05:37,916 --> 00:05:39,918
- "Don't get worked up."
- "Don't get worked up."

121
00:05:39,918 --> 00:05:42,788
"Sadness looks good on Sunny."

122
00:05:42,788 --> 00:05:44,122
[She's cringing hard]
Isn't it so funny?

123
00:05:44,122 --> 00:05:46,158
That is adorable. She really put in the work.

124
00:05:46,158 --> 00:05:48,560
- She got so specific with this!
- Seriously.

125
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:49,560
Isn't this so cute?

126
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:52,163
"Keep it cool unless I'm in the afterlife."

127
00:05:53,198 --> 00:05:55,901
"Innocent, but charismatic."

128
00:05:55,901 --> 00:05:57,669
[Kicking her feet]
"Always sit up straight.

129
00:05:57,669 --> 00:05:59,271
Don't overdo the expressions.

130
00:05:59,271 --> 00:06:00,272
Use breath and movement.

131
00:06:00,272 --> 00:06:01,573
Talk like you're really talking.

132
00:06:01,573 --> 00:06:04,176
Don't be too loud. Don't over-enunciate."

133
00:06:04,176 --> 00:06:06,611
That's insanely detailed.

134
00:06:06,611 --> 00:06:08,780
But that's exactly Sunny.

135
00:06:08,780 --> 00:06:10,048
So you pasted it in like this.

136
00:06:10,048 --> 00:06:12,684
I kept worrying I'd forget,
so I copied it into every script,

137
00:06:12,684 --> 00:06:14,386
like, "Don't forget this."

138
00:06:14,386 --> 00:06:15,821
That's why I wrote it down.

139
00:06:15,821 --> 00:06:17,221
And you really did it that way.

140
00:06:17,221 --> 00:06:21,326
[The hard work that made Sunny]
- Exactly. - I'm so embarrassed. Seriously.

141
00:06:21,326 --> 00:06:24,629
- Don't ever throw this away.
- That Post-it is so cute.

142
00:06:24,629 --> 00:06:26,264
Even this will probably make you laugh

143
00:06:26,264 --> 00:06:27,399
- when you see it ten years from now.
- Right. Back then,

144
00:06:27,399 --> 00:06:30,736
[A glimpse into their passion]
it'll feel like such a memory.

145
00:06:30,736 --> 00:06:34,064
<i>♪ You're so pretty, so pretty ♪</i>

146
00:06:34,064 --> 00:06:36,760
<i>♪ I'm telling you, you're so pretty ♪</i>

147
00:06:36,760 --> 00:06:38,210
[Giggling away]

148
00:06:38,210 --> 00:06:40,112
- In Na.
- Yeah?

149
00:06:40,112 --> 00:06:42,047
Did you try the snacks?

150
00:06:42,047 --> 00:06:44,082
- What? What is it?
- You know what these are, right?

151
00:06:44,082 --> 00:06:46,426
- They're so good. Try one, In Na.
- I love these.

152
00:06:46,426 --> 00:06:47,552
Have some of these snacks.

153
00:06:47,552 --> 00:06:48,820
You can buy these in Japan.

154
00:06:48,820 --> 00:06:50,622
- I told you I work at that store.
- Right.

155
00:06:50,622 --> 00:06:53,391
- Japanese fans?
- When fans from Japan drop by,

156
00:06:53,391 --> 00:06:55,127
[That is so touching]
they'd bring these for me

157
00:06:55,127 --> 00:06:57,195
[A gift she fell for]
and tell me to snack on them for energy.

158
00:06:57,195 --> 00:06:59,164
- I tried them, and they were so good.
- They really are good.

159
00:06:59,164 --> 00:07:00,932
- Try one.
- These are so good.

160
00:07:00,932 --> 00:07:02,934
[Let me have a bite]
I really needed this right now.

161
00:07:02,934 --> 00:07:05,303
It's not just chocolate.
It has macadamia in it, too.

162
00:07:05,303 --> 00:07:07,539
This is a seriously good snack.

163
00:07:07,539 --> 00:07:09,074
These are really good.

164
00:07:09,074 --> 00:07:11,476
- Aren't they so good?
- I really needed this.

165
00:07:11,476 --> 00:07:13,044
- Cute.
- Really?

166
00:07:13,044 --> 00:07:15,847
[Sugar boost complete]
I really needed it.

167
00:07:15,847 --> 00:07:17,249
The sound of the waves is so nice.

168
00:07:17,249 --> 00:07:20,485
- Wait, that was the waves?
- Yes.

169
00:07:21,286 --> 00:07:26,391
[Now for a romantic wave recharge]

170
00:07:26,391 --> 00:07:28,326
This is so nice.

171
00:07:28,326 --> 00:07:30,395
Hurry up, Goblin.

172
00:07:30,395 --> 00:07:32,224
[Coming]

173
00:07:32,831 --> 00:07:33,999
Look at him running over.

174
00:07:33,999 --> 00:07:37,836
[Team Goblin is all here]

175
00:07:37,836 --> 00:07:38,937
Okay.

176
00:07:38,937 --> 00:07:40,605
[Why are they in the yard?]

177
00:07:40,605 --> 00:07:43,208
- Starting now, I'm...
- Starting now.

178
00:07:43,208 --> 00:07:45,043
- I'm going to give you a quiz.
- Okay.

179
00:07:45,043 --> 00:07:46,645
Now we're going to...

180
00:07:46,645 --> 00:07:48,714
[Time for Goblin recreation]
play a little game.

181
00:07:48,714 --> 00:07:50,816
- You've all found your calm,
- Yes.

182
00:07:50,816 --> 00:07:52,217
and your minds are in good shape, right?

183
00:07:52,217 --> 00:07:53,218
- You're feeling sharp?
- Yes.

184
00:07:53,218 --> 00:07:54,386
- Yes.
- Okay.

185
00:07:54,386 --> 00:07:55,487
You're sharp right now?

186
00:07:55,487 --> 00:07:56,555
I feel a little drunk.

187
00:07:56,555 --> 00:07:57,556
- You're drunk?
- Yes.

188
00:07:57,556 --> 00:08:01,092
Then no one here has to think of you
as competition.

189
00:08:01,092 --> 00:08:03,128
[MC Sunny's solo Goblin quiz]
This is a scene

190
00:08:03,128 --> 00:08:04,596
everyone in Korea loves.

191
00:08:04,596 --> 00:08:07,933
- There are three rounds total.
- Okay.

192
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:10,302
[Trivia and famous lines]
As of 2026,

193
00:08:10,302 --> 00:08:12,804
how old is Kim Shin the Goblin?

194
00:08:12,804 --> 00:08:14,039
- Go Eun.
- Kyung Hye.

195
00:08:14,039 --> 00:08:15,106
[Shout your call sign to answer]
Necklace.

196
00:08:15,106 --> 00:08:16,326
- Goblin.
- Go Eun.

197
00:08:16,326 --> 00:08:17,843
[Quiz time heats up]
- Goblin! - Go Eun!

198
00:08:17,843 --> 00:08:20,278
- Goblin!
- Sit down.

199
00:08:20,278 --> 00:08:21,479
At least give me half a point.

200
00:08:21,479 --> 00:08:23,215
Half a point.

201
00:08:23,215 --> 00:08:24,983
This isn't some game show jungle quiz.

202
00:08:24,983 --> 00:08:26,818
Everyone came to win.

203
00:08:26,818 --> 00:08:29,888
[Goblin superfan mode on]
I'm a huge fan of Guardian.

204
00:08:29,888 --> 00:08:32,727
[Focused]
The top two players here

205
00:08:32,727 --> 00:08:34,793
will get a huge prize.

206
00:08:34,793 --> 00:08:36,928
- Is there really a prize?
- There really is.

207
00:08:36,928 --> 00:08:38,163
You won't tell us ahead of time?

208
00:08:38,163 --> 00:08:39,197
You won't reveal it?

209
00:08:39,197 --> 00:08:40,897
They already told me.

210
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:44,236
- In Guardian...
- Yes.

211
00:08:44,236 --> 00:08:45,503
- Eun Tak...
- Yes.

212
00:08:45,503 --> 00:08:47,838
what did she love most?

213
00:08:48,540 --> 00:08:50,001
What?

214
00:08:50,809 --> 00:08:52,711
- Money!
- Money!

215
00:08:52,711 --> 00:08:54,012
Five million won.

216
00:08:54,012 --> 00:08:55,981
What did she love after that?

217
00:08:55,981 --> 00:08:56,797
Her boyfriend?

218
00:08:56,797 --> 00:08:57,883
[Me?]

219
00:08:57,883 --> 00:08:59,851
A bag.

220
00:08:59,851 --> 00:09:01,987
[The Goblin loses to a bag]
- Perfume. - Perfume.

221
00:09:01,987 --> 00:09:03,521
Something more expensive than perfume.

222
00:09:03,521 --> 00:09:05,590
- Beef?
- Beef!

223
00:09:05,590 --> 00:09:06,925
- Right.
- Seriously?

224
00:09:06,925 --> 00:09:08,360
Seriously?

225
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,328
[She ate it on dates]

226
00:09:10,328 --> 00:09:11,529
I finally got the job.

227
00:09:11,529 --> 00:09:13,098
[Even Goblin ate it alone]
The boss is really pretty.

228
00:09:13,098 --> 00:09:16,201
[A slab of beef often seen in Guardian]

229
00:09:16,201 --> 00:09:17,636
It's beautiful.

230
00:09:17,636 --> 00:09:19,071
[The Reaper is vegetarian]

231
00:09:20,272 --> 00:09:22,941
[First Prize: Eun Tak's hanwoo]

232
00:09:22,941 --> 00:09:25,443
I'll be giving you her favorite hanwoo.

233
00:09:25,443 --> 00:09:27,545
[Proper motivation]
Give it your best.

234
00:09:27,545 --> 00:09:29,214
The MC is so generous.

235
00:09:29,214 --> 00:09:30,582
I'm already...

236
00:09:30,582 --> 00:09:32,484
I'm already liking this.

237
00:09:32,484 --> 00:09:34,386
No, no.

238
00:09:34,386 --> 00:09:36,671
[Go Eun charms MC Sunny]
I'm just here to do my best.

239
00:09:36,671 --> 00:09:40,216
But the questions are all things
you should be able to answer.

240
00:09:40,216 --> 00:09:41,360
They're about Guardian?

241
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:43,962
Of course. Every question is about Guardian.

242
00:09:43,962 --> 00:09:45,196
- Okay.
- Sounds good.

243
00:09:45,196 --> 00:09:47,065
[Warm-up Quiz]
Let's start Round 1.

244
00:09:47,065 --> 00:09:48,099
- Yeah.
- Round 1.

245
00:09:48,099 --> 00:09:49,968
In Guardian,

246
