- Yeah.

1003
00:36:06,877 --> 00:36:08,111
Thank you.

1004
00:36:08,111 --> 00:36:09,526
[Sunny lines Goblin loves most]
Are you poor?

1005
00:36:09,526 --> 00:36:11,181
I don't have one.

1006
00:36:11,181 --> 00:36:12,516
You don't have a phone?

1007
00:36:12,516 --> 00:36:13,917
Are you poor?

1008
00:36:13,917 --> 00:36:16,319
How about one more drink?

1009
00:36:19,456 --> 00:36:22,293
Did you just fly away?

1010
00:36:22,293 --> 00:36:24,992
- Are you a bird?
- What's wrong with me?

1011
00:36:24,992 --> 00:36:27,030
- I like that delivery.
- Right.

1012
00:36:27,030 --> 00:36:29,159
- Do it for us.
- Me?

1013
00:36:29,159 --> 00:36:31,033
[Sunny summoned]
Are you poor?

1014
00:36:32,235 --> 00:36:33,470
[Satisfied]
Okay.

1015
00:36:33,470 --> 00:36:35,005
To pull out the Goblin's sword,

1016
00:36:35,005 --> 00:36:36,926
the Shin-Tak couple comes
to the buckwheat field.

1017
00:36:36,926 --> 00:36:39,809
[What does Goblin say in the buckwheat field?]
It's from Episode 6. Let's watch.

1018
00:36:41,192 --> 00:36:43,493
[A legendary scene everyone knows]
We can probably all get this one.

1019
00:36:43,493 --> 00:36:45,293
Okay, then.

1020
00:36:45,293 --> 00:36:47,617
Let's make you beautiful now.

1021
00:36:47,617 --> 00:36:50,220
Any last words?

1022
00:36:50,220 --> 00:36:54,221
Every moment I spent with you was dazzling.

1023
00:37:04,868 --> 00:37:10,240
[This time, it's a pretty long line]

1024
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:13,176
[Glancing at the lead]

1025
00:37:13,176 --> 00:37:14,818
[Back on her feet at last]

1026
00:37:14,818 --> 00:37:15,859
Goblin.

1027
00:37:15,859 --> 00:37:17,347
- This one is...
- Goblin.

1028
00:37:17,347 --> 00:37:18,348
Goblin.

1029
00:37:18,348 --> 00:37:20,183
[I know this one too...]
- This one is... - Goblin.

1030
00:37:20,183 --> 00:37:22,593
[Blank mind]

1031
00:37:22,593 --> 00:37:25,004
- He should obviously get this.
- It's the one from earlier.

1032
00:37:25,004 --> 00:37:26,356
You know this one.

1033
00:37:26,356 --> 00:37:27,892
[The true Goblin fan seems lost]
Kyung Hye.

1034
00:37:27,892 --> 00:37:30,660
- The one we saw earlier.
- Kyung Hye. That one from earlier.

1035
00:37:30,660 --> 00:37:31,660
Goblin.

1036
00:37:31,660 --> 00:37:34,560
"Because the day was good,
because the day wasn't good..."

1037
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:35,865
- I can't remember the rest.
- Wrong.

1038
00:37:35,865 --> 00:37:36,866
- Go Eun.
- Go Eun.

1039
00:37:36,866 --> 00:37:38,126
- I can't remember the rest.
- Wrong.

1040
00:37:38,126 --> 00:37:39,936
[Whining]
- Go Eun. - Go Eun.

1041
00:37:39,936 --> 00:37:41,738
[The chance goes to Go Eun]
Go Eun.

1042
00:37:41,738 --> 00:37:44,743
"Because the day was good,
because the day wasn't good..."

1043
00:37:44,743 --> 00:37:47,393
[Counting the words]
- "Because the day was just right." - Samshin.

1044
00:37:47,393 --> 00:37:49,593
"Because the day was just right.
Every day was good."

1045
00:37:49,593 --> 00:37:51,414
Correct.

1046
00:37:52,426 --> 00:37:53,717
Correct.

1047
00:37:53,717 --> 00:37:56,360
[She gets the longest line right]

1048
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:57,593
That's right.

1049
00:37:57,593 --> 00:37:59,055
"Because the day was just right."

1050
00:37:59,055 --> 00:38:01,491
[Goblin's famous line stolen by Eun Tak]

1051
00:38:01,491 --> 00:38:03,859
Go Eun is so sharp.

1052
00:38:03,859 --> 00:38:05,261
She knows everything.

1053
00:38:05,261 --> 00:38:07,783
[Turns out Go Eun is a quiz powerhouse]
She's amazing.

1054
00:38:08,460 --> 00:38:10,900
[Answer revealed]
Any last words?

1055
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:12,968
Because the day was good,

1056
00:38:13,672 --> 00:38:16,206
because the day wasn't good...

1057
00:38:16,206 --> 00:38:17,360
"Because the day was just right."

1058
00:38:17,360 --> 00:38:20,043
Because the day was just right.

1059
00:38:20,043 --> 00:38:22,278
Every day was good.

1060
00:38:22,278 --> 00:38:24,613
Okay, then. I'll pull it out now.

1061
00:38:29,626 --> 00:38:33,089
Why can't I grab it?

1062
00:38:33,727 --> 00:38:36,793
I figured it out. I think I know what this is.

1063
00:38:36,793 --> 00:38:38,336
What is it?

1064
00:38:39,827 --> 00:38:41,965
A kiss!

1065
00:38:41,965 --> 00:38:45,501
[Eun Tak's bold kiss]

1066
00:38:49,673 --> 00:38:51,608
- This was your first shoot?
- Yeah, our first shoot.

1067
00:38:51,608 --> 00:38:54,346
- This was your first shoot?
- Yeah, it was our first shoot.

1068
00:38:54,346 --> 00:38:56,259
[Their first shoot: the buckwheat field kiss]
Really?

1069
00:38:56,259 --> 00:38:58,381
Right after we said hi.

1070
00:38:59,293 --> 00:39:00,493
Right.

1071
00:39:00,493 --> 00:39:04,988
But we really shot that kiss
from so many angles.

1072
00:39:04,988 --> 00:39:06,523
- Oh, really?
- Then you must've kissed a lot.

1073
00:39:06,523 --> 00:39:09,660
We really did kiss from a lot of angles.

1074
00:39:09,660 --> 00:39:11,161
It was a scene they put a lot into.

1075
00:39:11,161 --> 00:39:13,793
This whole location was.

1076
00:39:13,793 --> 00:39:16,560
When you left that morning,

1077
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:20,593
did you think, "I'm kissing today?"

1078
00:39:20,593 --> 00:39:22,105
[A question on another level]
Who thinks that?

1079
00:39:22,105 --> 00:39:23,306
I did. I did think that.

1080
00:39:23,306 --> 00:39:24,641
- Right?
- Yeah, I did.

1081
00:39:24,641 --> 00:39:25,942
"I'm kissing Gong Yoo."

1082
00:39:25,942 --> 00:39:27,711
Yeah, exactly. I thought that too.

1083
00:39:27,711 --> 00:39:29,579
I loved it so much.

1084
00:39:29,579 --> 00:39:32,006
[Cheeky]
I still remember it.

1085
00:39:32,006 --> 00:39:33,556
It's a really precious scene to me.

1086
00:39:33,556 --> 00:39:34,592
- Really?
- Same for me.

1087
00:39:34,592 --> 00:39:36,219
- Yes.
- This is so much fun.

1088
00:39:36,219 --> 00:39:38,888
Okay, next question.

1089
00:39:39,522 --> 00:39:42,459
[Q. What does Sunny say on their first call?]
It's Sunny and Grim Reaper's first phone call.

1090
00:39:42,459 --> 00:39:44,294
[Already looks lost]
Their first call, from Episode 5.

1091
00:39:44,294 --> 00:39:46,262
Watch closely.

1092
00:39:46,262 --> 00:39:48,098
[S# Grim Reaper and Sunny's first call]
I was waiting for your call.

1093
00:39:48,098 --> 00:39:50,500
Oh, yes.

1094
00:39:50,500 --> 00:39:51,935
"Oh, yes."

1095
00:39:51,935 --> 00:39:54,070
Is that all?

1096
00:39:54,070 --> 00:39:56,039
<i>- Don't you have something else to say?</i>
- This scene...

1097
00:39:56,039 --> 00:39:57,240
I remember it, but...

1098
00:39:57,240 --> 00:39:58,126
For example...

1099
00:39:58,126 --> 00:40:01,277
Like asking if morning, afternoon,
or evening works best?

1100
00:40:01,277 --> 00:40:02,912
Between morning, afternoon, and evening,

1101
00:40:02,912 --> 00:40:05,181
which time works best for you?

1102
00:40:06,583 --> 00:40:11,159
[5-star difficulty]
[What does Sunny say?]

1103
00:40:11,159 --> 00:40:12,360
Huh?

1104
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:14,156
Why is it so long?

1105
00:40:16,439 --> 00:40:18,706
"Whether we meet in the morning or at night..."

1106
00:40:18,706 --> 00:40:19,742
Yeah, it's something like that.

1107
00:40:19,742 --> 00:40:21,436
- That's the idea, right?
- Yeah, exactly.

1108
00:40:21,436 --> 00:40:22,999
No, no.

1109
00:40:22,999 --> 00:40:24,453
If it's "in the morning,"
then the spacing isn't correct.

1110
00:40:24,453 --> 00:40:26,668
- Oh, you're right.
- Alright.

1111
00:40:26,668 --> 00:40:28,569
Okay, let me try it once

1112
00:40:28,569 --> 00:40:32,665
using just the melody, without the lyrics.

1113
00:40:32,665 --> 00:40:34,374
I'll give you only the first two syllables.

1114
00:40:34,374 --> 00:40:35,598
- Okay.
- Yeah.

1115
00:40:35,598 --> 00:40:39,639
[In the silence, ready to shout the answer...]

1116
00:40:39,639 --> 00:40:43,937
"As for me..."

1117
00:40:43,937 --> 00:40:47,451
"As for me..."

1118
00:40:47,451 --> 00:40:48,475
[Huh?]

1119
00:40:48,475 --> 00:40:51,749
I think that's it. "As for me, whether we meet
in the morning or at night..."

1120
00:40:51,749 --> 00:40:53,571
"Meet in the morning..."

1121
00:40:53,571 --> 00:40:56,633
- Wait! Please say your name first.
- Oh, alright.

1122
00:40:56,633 --> 00:40:58,584
[Trying again after a long time]
- Joong Heon. - Joong Heon!

1123
00:40:58,584 --> 00:40:59,617
"As for me...

1124
00:40:59,617 --> 00:41:02,200
if we meet in the morning

1125
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:05,002
and part ways at night..."

1126
00:41:05,002 --> 00:41:07,278
Watch the syllable count.

1127
00:41:07,278 --> 00:41:09,631
[Big hint]
Doing what?

1128
00:41:09,631 --> 00:41:11,051
[Lost for words]

1129
00:41:11,051 --> 00:41:12,587
- I don't know the rest.
- No, wait...

1130
00:41:12,587 --> 00:41:14,986
Aww, I feel bad for you.
I'll give you a pity point.

1131
00:41:14,986 --> 00:41:16,021
I'll give you a pity point.

1132
00:41:16,021 --> 00:41:17,490
I have no idea what comes next.

1133
00:41:17,490 --> 00:41:20,406
Oh, I feel so bad for him.
I'll give him a pity point.

1134
00:41:20,406 --> 00:41:23,453
[Quickly jumping in]
I've got it! Samshin! Can I steal the answer...

1135
00:41:23,453 --> 00:41:25,116
Ah, Samshin, Samshin, Samshin!

1136
00:41:25,116 --> 00:41:26,541
Oh, she told me not to stand up.

1137
00:41:26,541 --> 00:41:28,596
She follows the rules well.

1138
00:41:28,596 --> 00:41:30,254
Give her a point for following the rules.

1139
00:41:30,254 --> 00:41:33,646
- You get a rule point, Samshin.
- Wow!

1140
00:41:33,646 --> 00:41:37,271
[MC Sunny is generous with the guests]
- Wow! - Alright.

1141
00:41:37,271 --> 00:41:39,092
Okay, start!

1142
00:41:39,092 --> 00:41:40,122
"As for me...

1143
00:41:40,122 --> 00:41:44,815
I'd rather meet in the morning
and part ways at night."

1144
00:41:44,815 --> 00:41:47,150
- No, that's not it!
- Goblin!

1145
00:41:47,150 --> 00:41:48,323
[Goblin jumps in after Samshin misses]

1146
00:41:48,323 --> 00:41:50,164
- No, that's not it!
- Oh, I got it wrong!

1147
00:41:50,164 --> 00:41:53,590
Goblin! Goblin!

1148
00:41:53,590 --> 00:41:55,859
"As for me...

1149
00:41:55,859 --> 00:42:01,790
meeting in the morning
and parting ways at night...

1150
00:42:01,790 --> 00:42:04,239
would be the best..." No, "the very best!"

1151
00:42:04,239 --> 00:42:06,394
- "Would be the very best." "The best..."
- Wrong!

1152
00:42:06,394 --> 00:42:07,626
Oh, are you kneeling?

1153
00:42:07,626 --> 00:42:09,128
You're actually kneeling? One point!

1154
00:42:09,128 --> 00:42:10,631
I'll give you a kneeling point.

1155
00:42:10,631 --> 00:42:13,129
[Goblin goes down on his knees for a point]

1156
00:42:14,177 --> 00:42:15,775
[They have no idea how serious he is
about this quiz]

1157
00:42:15,775 --> 00:42:18,110
Oh, I gave it to the Grim Reaper, though?

1158
00:42:18,110 --> 00:42:20,452
The last three syllables are wrong.

1159
00:42:20,452 --> 00:42:21,840
But let me ask you something.

1160
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:25,864
[Pay attention to the Grim Reaper's question]
Let me ask the Grim Reaper's question again.

1161
00:42:25,864 --> 00:42:27,203
"Morning, afternoon, or evening...

1162
00:42:27,203 --> 00:42:29,495
- which is the most convenient?"
- Oh, Samshin!

1163
00:42:29,495 --> 00:42:31,083
Go Eun!

1164
00:42:31,083 --> 00:42:32,108
Samshin!

1165
00:42:32,108 --> 00:42:34,146
"As for me, meeting in the morning

1166
00:42:34,146 --> 00:42:35,991
and parting ways at night
is the most convenient for me."

1167
00:42:35,991 --> 00:42:38,656
[Samshin finally gets it right]
- Correct! - Oh, that's right.

1168
00:42:38,656 --> 00:42:42,899
See? That's why teachers always tell you
to read the question carefully!

1169
00:42:42,899 --> 00:42:46,126
- The answer was in the question.
- Right.

1170
00:42:46,903 --> 00:42:48,456
[Answer revealed]
Morning, afternoon, or evening,

1171
00:42:48,456 --> 00:42:49,778
which is the most convenient?

1172
00:42:49,778 --> 00:42:53,579
As for me, meeting in the morning and
parting ways at night is the most convenient.

1173
00:42:53,579 --> 00:42:55,650
[Without numbers,
the Grim Reaper is completely lost]

1174
00:42:55,650 --> 00:42:56,763
That's why teachers tell you

1175
00:42:56,763 --> 00:42:58,549
- to read the questions carefully...
- Teachers always say to read carefully.

1176
00:42:58,549 --> 00:43:02,078
But isn't this line just so good?

1177
00:43:02,078 --> 00:43:03,960
To someone you're interested in,

1178
00:43:03,960 --> 00:43:06,063
if you ask, "Morning, afternoon, or evening...

1179
00:43:06,063 --> 00:43:07,517
- which is the most convenient?"
- That's right.

1180
00:43:07,517 --> 00:43:09,658
"As for me, meeting in the morning and
parting ways at night is the most convenient."

1181
00:43:09,658 --> 00:43:11,345
Wouldn't that be such a sweet thing to say?

1182
00:43:11,345 --> 00:43:12,563
- It'd be wonderful.
- Absolutely. That would be wonderful.

1183
00:43:12,563 --> 00:43:15,124
- I'd be so happy if someone said that to me.
- Right? Your heart flutters, doesn't it?

1184
00:43:15,124 --> 00:43:16,530
Yeah, I'd be so excited, and...

1185
00:43:16,530 --> 00:43:18,809
- Oh... it'd be such a thrill.
- A thrill...

1186
00:43:18,809 --> 00:43:21,973
[Joong Heon's innocent charm
keeps growing on you]

1187
00:43:23,108 --> 00:43:24,539
[Just imagining it feels like heaven,
not disaster]

1188
00:43:24,539 --> 00:43:26,314
You're all trying so hard.

1189
00:43:26,314 --> 00:43:28,814
[On to the next thrilling question]
Alright, here's the next question.

1190
00:43:28,814 --> 00:43:32,210
[Q. Samshin's line at Eun Tak's graduation?]
Samshin shows up at Eun Tak's graduation!

1191
00:43:32,210 --> 00:43:35,133
- Huh? That's mine.
- Yes, it's from Episode 11.

1192
00:43:35,133 --> 00:43:38,540
[S# Eun Tak's Graduation]

1193
00:43:43,651 --> 00:43:45,999
- It really was such a great scene. Right?
- Yeah.

1194
00:43:45,999 --> 00:43:48,209
- It was such a beautiful scene.
- Samshin was so amazing.

1195
00:43:48,209 --> 00:43:50,971
Why are you hugging me?

1196
00:43:52,458 --> 00:43:54,382
Because you're beautiful.

1197
00:44:01,475 --> 00:44:03,188
Aww...

1198
00:44:03,778 --> 00:44:06,164
- Aww...
- Quick, quick, quick!

1199
00:44:06,164 --> 00:44:08,704
- Samshin.
- Samshin!

1200
00:44:08,704 --> 00:44:10,639
"I was happy when I blessed you
with your fate."

1201
00:44:10,639 --> 00:44:12,341
Ah... it still moves me.

1202
00:44:12,341 --> 00:44:14,636
[Samshin's unforgettable line]
- I memorized this one too. I know it. - Right.

1203
00:44:14,636 --> 00:44:17,437
"I was happy when I blessed you
with your fate."

1204
00:44:17,437 --> 00:44:21,941
[Answer revealed]
Why are you hugging me?

1205
00:44:21,941 --> 00:44:26,152
I was happy...
when I blessed you with your fate.

1206
00:44:26,152 --> 00:44:27,941
I was happy.

1207
00:44:32,632 --> 00:44:34,228
My dear,

1208
00:44:34,942 --> 00:44:37,769
couldn't you have been a better teacher?

1209
00:44:38,577 --> 00:44:41,479
Couldn't you have been
a more brilliant teacher?

1210
00:44:52,977 --> 00:44:54,854
- What a wonderful scene.
- But seriously...

1211
00:44:54,854 --> 00:44:57,740
Lee El delivered that performance
so beautifully.

1212
00:44:57,740 --> 00:44:59,586
She really did an amazing job.

1213
00:44:59,586 --> 00:45:02,127
Without a single harsh word,

1214
00:45:02,127 --> 00:45:05,441
you just said, "Couldn't you have been
a more brilliant teacher?"

1215
00:45:05,441 --> 00:45:06,779
[Shy]
The line itself was just so good.

1216
00:45:06,779 --> 00:45:08,992
That's right. Our lines were all...

1217
00:45:08,992 --> 00:45:10,263
Every single line really was...

1218
00:45:10,263 --> 00:45:12,011
[Still touching after all these years]
- It was really... - Yeah.

1219
00:45:12,011 --> 00:45:17,345
I think these scenes where Eun Tak is comforted
were the most heartwarming.

1220
00:45:17,345 --> 00:45:20,647
- That's right.
- One of my favorite scenes is that one too.

1221
00:45:20,647 --> 00:45:24,939
When Deok Hwa and the two of you
surprised Eun Tak with a cake after her exam.

1222
00:45:24,939 --> 00:45:27,647
- That scene was really...
- That's right.

1223
00:45:27,647 --> 00:45:30,067
My brain worked so hard today. I'm exhausted...

1224
00:45:30,067 --> 00:45:31,607
[S# Celebration party
after Eun Tak's College Entrance Exam]

1225
00:45:31,607 --> 00:45:32,864
How did your exam go?

1226
00:45:32,864 --> 00:45:36,406
I came up with the idea, he paid for it,
and Deok Hwa bought it.

1227
00:45:36,406 --> 00:45:38,405
Wow...

1228
00:45:38,405 --> 00:45:40,539
it's a cake...

1229
00:45:40,539 --> 00:45:44,531
I'm so happy today,
so I'm going to make a wish.

1230
00:45:44,531 --> 00:45:47,142
Please let me go see a movie
with Mr. Goblin later.

1231
00:45:47,142 --> 00:45:49,304
And popcorn too, please.

1232
00:45:52,860 --> 00:45:54,498
- Huh?
- Huh?

1233
00:45:58,236 --> 00:46:00,695
- I remember that blooper.
- Yeah.

1234
00:46:00,695 --> 00:46:01,828
With Mr. Grim Reaper...

1235
00:46:01,828 --> 00:46:05,900
Originally, the wish was to go
see a movie with the Goblin.

1236
00:46:05,900 --> 00:46:07,685
- Then she added, "And popcorn too."
- Yeah, but she...

1237
00:46:07,685 --> 00:46:11,699
she suddenly said, "Please let me go
see a movie with Mr. Grim Reaper."

1238
00:46:11,699 --> 00:46:13,348
- That's how she made the blooper.
- That's right.

1239
00:46:13,348 --> 00:46:14,374
- The three of them...
- Really?

1240
00:46:14,374 --> 00:46:16,417
opened my eyes at the same time.

1241
00:46:16,417 --> 00:46:18,194
"With Mr. Grim Reaper?"

1242
00:46:19,268 --> 00:46:22,019
Please let me go see a movie
with Mr. Grim Reaper later.

1243
00:46:22,019 --> 00:46:24,671
And popcorn too, please.

1244
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:27,210
- With Mr. Grim Reaper?
- With Mr. Grim Reaper?

1245
00:46:28,219 --> 00:46:30,791
Don't cut the cameras! Don't cut the cameras!

1246
00:46:30,791 --> 00:46:33,167
This is a historic moment. Capture all of it!

1247
00:46:33,167 --> 00:46:34,879
That's right, that's right.

1248
00:46:34,879 --> 00:46:37,493
- I remember that.
- Yeah, I remember now.

1249
00:46:37,493 --> 00:46:39,013
[Curious, Next question?]

1250
00:46:39,013 --> 00:46:40,713
[No peeking!]

1251
00:46:41,457 --> 00:46:45,442
The Grim Reaper calls out Park Joong Heon,
who is about to be destroyed by the Goblin.

1252
00:46:45,442 --> 00:46:48,179
Let's watch. It's Episode 13.

1253
00:46:48,179 --> 00:46:50,946
[S# Kim Shin vs. Park Joong Heon]

1254
00:46:50,946 --> 00:46:52,742
Park Joong Heon!

1255
00:46:54,593 --> 00:46:58,609
The dead shall answer the Grim Reaper's call.

1256
00:46:58,609 --> 00:47:01,555
- You...
- Park Joong Heon!

1257
00:47:01,555 --> 00:47:04,059
Park Joong Heon!

1258
00:47:05,042 --> 00:47:06,866
He cut him here.

1259
00:47:06,866 --> 00:47:08,200
And then...

1260
00:47:08,200 --> 00:47:11,332
So this is how it ends for me...

1261
00:47:11,332 --> 00:47:13,911
But it is not in vain.

1262
00:47:13,911 --> 00:47:17,102
- For I have killed you once again.
- "I have killed you once again."

1263
00:47:17,102 --> 00:47:18,891
Look at that smile.

1264
00:47:23,519 --> 00:47:25,814
[A scene everyone knows from memes]

1265
00:47:25,814 --> 00:47:26,839
Oh!

1266
00:47:26,839 --> 00:47:28,057
- Oh...
- I know the last part, though.

1267
00:47:28,057 --> 00:47:32,362
- Just the last part.
- I can't remember the first three syllables.

1268
00:47:32,362 --> 00:47:33,817
"It's a disaster!"

1269
00:47:33,817 --> 00:47:37,334
- Can I answer too?
- Of course. Go ahead and answer.

1270
00:47:37,334 --> 00:47:39,031
How about giving them a chance first?

1271
00:47:39,031 --> 00:47:42,710
Wait. I'll count that as a correct answer for
showing consideration and give you one point.

1272
00:47:42,710 --> 00:47:45,156
- Wow, such generosity... yeah.
- Oh, the virtue of generosity?

1273
00:47:45,156 --> 00:47:46,187
Since he knows it,

1274
00:47:46,187 --> 00:47:47,532
- he wants to give someone else a chance.
- Go Eun!

1275
00:47:47,532 --> 00:47:51,430
- "Once again, it's a disaster."
- Oh, that's incorrect.

1276
00:47:52,255 --> 00:47:53,423
[Even now, the Grim Reaper
is looking out for the ghost]

1277
00:47:53,423 --> 00:47:55,396
- That's it! That's it!
- Hurry! Hurry!

1278
00:47:55,396 --> 00:47:57,270
Kyung Hye!

1279
00:47:57,270 --> 00:48:01,419
"Once again, it ends in disaster."

1280
00:48:02,155 --> 00:48:03,324
[Wrong]
Still, that was close.

1281
00:48:03,324 --> 00:48:05,366
- He says it was close!
- It's not "once again."

1282
00:48:05,366 --> 00:48:06,994
Can we give them a little hint?

1283
00:48:06,994 --> 00:48:09,277
Here's a hint.

1284
00:48:09,277 --> 00:48:13,896
"See... Finally... Pakook-ida!"

1285
00:48:13,896 --> 00:48:18,278
"See... Finally... Pakook-ida!"

1286
00:48:18,278 --> 00:48:21,129
- Goblin! Goblin!
- "Behold! Behold!"

1287
00:48:21,129 --> 00:48:22,532
- "Behold."
- Yeah.

1288
00:48:22,532 --> 00:48:23,720
- "In the end!"
- "Behold."

1289
00:48:23,720 --> 00:48:25,951
- "In the end, it's a disaster."
- Why is she giving him all the answers?

1290
00:48:25,951 --> 00:48:28,304
[Correct answer! Jeongdap-ida]
Correct!

1291
00:48:28,304 --> 00:48:29,527
- Correct!
- "Behold."

1292
00:48:29,527 --> 00:48:31,419
Wow, that English hint was awesome.

1293
00:48:31,419 --> 00:48:34,280
- Pretty good, huh?
- That caught me off guard.

1294
00:48:34,280 --> 00:48:36,386
[Answer revealed]

1295
00:48:39,020 --> 00:48:41,560
But it is not in vain.

1296
00:48:41,560 --> 00:48:43,260
[See]
Behold.

1297
00:48:44,787 --> 00:48:46,487
[Finally]
In the end...

1298
00:48:47,885 --> 00:48:49,043
[Pakook-ida]
it's a disaster.

1299
00:48:49,043 --> 00:48:50,987
Ah! So scary!

1300
00:48:52,039 --> 00:48:54,847
- That's so scary.
- So scary.

1301
00:48:54,847 --> 00:48:57,238
Whoa, he disappeared.

1302
00:48:57,238 --> 00:49:00,739
[Then the Goblin leaves Eun Tak...]

1303
00:49:00,739 --> 00:49:04,889
- Oh, just hearing her cry makes me tear up.
- Meeting you...

1304
00:49:05,516 --> 00:49:06,698
my life was a reward.

1305
00:49:06,698 --> 00:49:09,410
No! Don't go! Goblin, don't leave!

1306
00:49:09,410 --> 00:49:11,110
No!

1307
00:49:12,449 --> 00:49:14,149
Please...

1308
00:49:19,477 --> 00:49:22,180
You said you'd never let go of my hand.

1309
00:49:24,165 --> 00:49:25,920
You promised.

1310
00:49:25,920 --> 00:49:27,936
I'll come back as the rain.

1311
00:49:27,936 --> 00:49:30,049
I'll come back as the first snow.

1312
00:49:30,049 --> 00:49:33,182
I'll pray that I'm allowed to do at least that.

1313
00:49:34,712 --> 00:49:37,341
I'll pray to God.

1314
00:49:37,341 --> 00:49:41,417
Mister... I love you. I love you.

1315
00:49:44,508 --> 00:49:46,358
I do too...

1316
00:49:54,265 --> 00:49:56,209
I love you.

1317
00:50:07,219 --> 00:50:13,203
[Eun Tak cries out in despair, left all alone]

1318
00:50:19,095 --> 00:50:20,771
Seriously...

1319
00:50:20,771 --> 00:50:22,976
Ah... seriously...

1320
00:50:22,976 --> 00:50:25,428
The best. Absolutely the best.

1321
00:50:25,428 --> 00:50:26,753
- The best.
- Wow...

1322
00:50:26,753 --> 00:50:29,031
- But it was unbelievably cold that day.
- Right.

1323
00:50:29,031 --> 00:50:31,090
- And we were on a rooftop.
- Yeah, it really was.

1324
00:50:31,090 --> 00:50:32,637
- That was in Yeouido...
- Right.

1325
00:50:32,637 --> 00:50:34,096
- It was really...
- Right.

1326
00:50:34,096 --> 00:50:36,393
- I still remember it.
- It was on the rooftop.

1327
00:50:36,393 --> 00:50:40,004
Out of everything I've ever filmed,
I remember that as the coldest moment.

1328
00:50:40,004 --> 00:50:41,792
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1329
00:50:41,792 --> 00:50:43,876
So whenever they called "Cut," everyone...

1330
00:50:43,876 --> 00:50:45,456
- Everyone ran inside.
- Everyone ran off, right?

1331
00:50:45,456 --> 00:50:48,167
- ran to the emergency stairs.
- Everyone rushed toward the stairwell.

1332
00:50:48,167 --> 00:50:50,045
- Everyone did.
- Look, my ears were bright red.

1333
00:50:50,045 --> 00:50:52,285
- You're right.
- Yeah.

1334
00:50:52,893 --> 00:50:54,602
[Frozen ears]

1335
00:50:54,602 --> 00:50:58,280
The thing is, it was so cold...

1336
00:50:58,280 --> 00:51:01,292
my head went numb,
and the pressure kept building.

1337
00:51:01,292 --> 00:51:04,607
When everyone was basically
becoming fools together in that situation...

1338
00:51:04,607 --> 00:51:06,743
- I felt pressured...
- Right.

1339
00:51:06,743 --> 00:51:08,115
- because I wanted to pull it off for them.
- That must have been stressful.

1340
00:51:08,115 --> 00:51:11,292
Then Director Lee Eung Bok stopped the shoot.

1341
00:51:11,292 --> 00:51:13,534
He said, "We'll just pull the camera back."

1342
00:51:13,534 --> 00:51:15,802
The moment the camera pulled away...

1343
00:51:15,802 --> 00:51:18,386
I finally let everything go,

1344
00:51:18,386 --> 00:51:20,883
and the emotions just poured out.

1345
00:51:20,883 --> 00:51:26,304
So that's why that crying felt so real.

1346
00:51:26,304 --> 00:51:29,241
Yeah, scenes like this
come with so much pressure.

1347
00:51:29,241 --> 00:51:33,588
- If I couldn't break into tears quickly...
- The pressure to pull it off...

1348
00:51:33,588 --> 00:51:39,317
the entire crew had to keep shivering
in the cold waiting for me.

1349
00:51:39,317 --> 00:51:40,605
That's right.

1350
00:51:40,605 --> 00:51:42,225
But you know what?

1351
00:51:42,225 --> 00:51:45,023
Remember that time?
When you're in a situation like that,

1352
00:51:45,023 --> 00:51:47,485
there's always that one person
on the directing team.

1353
00:51:47,485 --> 00:51:48,795
"Quiet, everyone!"

1354
00:51:48,795 --> 00:51:49,801
You know what I mean, right?

1355
00:51:49,801 --> 00:51:51,359
"Quiet, everyone!"

1356
00:51:51,359 --> 00:51:53,778
[And the emotion is gone]
You know what I mean, right?

1357
00:51:53,778 --> 00:51:56,137
- "It's an emotional scene! Be quiet!"
- "Be quiet!"

1358
00:51:56,137 --> 00:51:58,025
Then comes the important part.

1359
00:51:58,025 --> 00:51:59,937
"Let us know when you're ready."

1360
00:51:59,937 --> 00:52:02,516
[Pressure]
- Then, I'm like... - It's so much pressure.

1361
00:52:02,516 --> 00:52:03,974
- Everyone's staring only at me.
- Right.

1362
00:52:03,974 --> 00:52:05,317
They're all holding their radios
and staring at me.

1363
00:52:05,317 --> 00:52:07,340
- That just makes it even harder.
- Exactly.

1364
00:52:07,340 --> 00:52:08,594
But they're just

1365
00:52:08,594 --> 00:52:11,477
- doing their job as best they can.
- Right.

1366
00:52:11,477 --> 00:52:14,833
[Another behind-the-scenes story]
Back then, I was wearing hair extensions.

1367
00:52:14,833 --> 00:52:17,183
Eun Tak's long hair was actually extensions.

1368
00:52:17,183 --> 00:52:18,464
- Glued-in extensions.
- Yeah.

1369
00:52:18,464 --> 00:52:23,284
But I kept those glued-in extensions on
for three or four days.

1370
00:52:23,284 --> 00:52:26,451
Taking them off and putting them
back on took an hour and a half.

1371
00:52:26,451 --> 00:52:28,642
- So you just kept them on.
- We didn't have the time.

1372
00:52:28,642 --> 00:52:31,559
After Guardian ended, I actually...

1373
00:52:31,559 --> 00:52:33,242
- started losing my hair.
- I think you mentioned that before.

1374
00:52:33,242 --> 00:52:35,200
- Yeah.
- That's really rough.

1375
00:52:35,200 --> 00:52:37,584
- It really was.
- I honestly don't know how you got through it.

1376
00:52:37,584 --> 00:52:39,944
- Right? I don't think I could do it now.
- Seriously...

1377
00:52:39,944 --> 00:52:42,403
Alright, only three questions left.

1378
00:52:42,403 --> 00:52:44,628
[I'm getting this one!]
Now, the next question

1379
00:52:44,628 --> 00:52:45,658
takes place on the overpass.

1380
00:52:45,658 --> 00:52:49,052
This is the scene where Sunny and
the Grim Reaper say their final goodbye.

1381
00:52:49,052 --> 00:52:50,281
[I'll get this one!]

1382
00:52:50,281 --> 00:52:52,593
[S# Grim Reaper and Sunny's farewell]
So,

1383
00:52:52,593 --> 00:52:55,719
by dying, I protected you...

1384
00:52:55,719 --> 00:52:57,561
Did that become a happy ending for you?

1385
00:52:57,561 --> 00:52:59,493
- Yeah... this scene is heartbreaking.
- The scene you find the saddest.

1386
00:52:59,493 --> 00:53:01,650
- This is Dong Wook's favorite scene.
- Right.

1387
00:53:02,316 --> 00:53:04,102
Because...

1388
00:53:07,119 --> 00:53:09,387
I miss you so much...

1389
00:53:09,387 --> 00:53:13,208
Here it is. Let's really say goodbye now.

1390
00:53:13,208 --> 00:53:15,711
I won't fall for you in this lifetime.

1391
00:53:16,582 --> 00:53:19,907
That's the only punishment...

1392
00:53:19,907 --> 00:53:21,970
I can give you.

1393
00:53:31,281 --> 00:53:38,762
[Not even trying to answer,
completely absorbed in the drama]

1394
00:53:40,160 --> 00:53:41,787
- Ah!
- Ah!

1395
00:53:41,787 --> 00:53:43,307
- Goblin!
- Goblin!

1396
00:53:43,307 --> 00:53:44,838
- Ah!
- Goblin!

1397
00:53:44,838 --> 00:53:46,617
[You have to call your name first, LOL]
Goblin!

1398
00:53:46,617 --> 00:53:48,918
[The chance goes to the Goblin]
Goblin.

1399
00:53:48,918 --> 00:53:49,963
"Goodbye, Your Majesty."

1400
00:53:49,963 --> 00:53:52,208
- Oh, correct! Wow!
- Yeah! That's right!

1401
00:53:52,208 --> 00:53:54,598
- How could you let him steal that from you?
- I couldn't even remember my own name.

1402
00:53:54,598 --> 00:53:55,983
Jeez...

1403
00:53:55,983 --> 00:53:57,008
[Nice]

1404
00:53:57,008 --> 00:53:59,804
These people are unbelievably competitive.

1405
00:53:59,804 --> 00:54:01,624
The Goblin's competitive spirit is no joke.

1406
00:54:01,624 --> 00:54:03,501
[Releasing 949 years of competitive spirit]
The competitive spirit is unreal.

1407
00:54:03,501 --> 00:54:06,628
[Answer revealed]
Let's really say goodbye now.

1408
00:54:07,305 --> 00:54:09,235
Goodbye, Your Majesty.

1409
00:54:16,129 --> 00:54:17,740
I mentioned this in the car earlier.

1410
00:54:17,740 --> 00:54:20,761
There are two scenes from Guardian
that always make me the saddest.

1411
00:54:20,761 --> 00:54:22,372
This is one of them.

1412
00:54:22,372 --> 00:54:24,643
After they part like this...

1413
00:54:24,643 --> 00:54:28,319
there's the scene where he meets
Sunny again at the café.

1414
00:54:28,319 --> 00:54:30,554
That scene is so heartbreaking.

1415
00:54:30,554 --> 00:54:32,597
- Back then, I really...
- Me too. I felt the same.

1416
00:54:32,597 --> 00:54:34,089
The two of us were sitting there that day...

1417
00:54:34,089 --> 00:54:35,174
- You're crying?
- the whole time...

1418
00:54:35,174 --> 00:54:36,424
You're crying?

1419
00:54:36,424 --> 00:54:37,889
[Sob]
Are you crying?

1420
00:54:37,889 --> 00:54:40,115
[Crying from laughter]
[Crying from sadness]

1421
00:54:40,115 --> 00:54:41,525
[A bittersweet scene that still makes her cry]
It made her cry.

1422
00:54:41,525 --> 00:54:44,066
I really couldn't get my lines out
in that scene.

1423
00:54:44,066 --> 00:54:45,639
My throat was so choked up.

1424
00:54:45,639 --> 00:54:48,550
So neither of us could say our lines.

1425
00:54:50,020 --> 00:54:51,196
Do you know who I am?

1426
00:54:51,196 --> 00:54:52,737
[S# Sunny and the Grim Reaper reunite,
pretending not to remember each other]

1427
00:54:52,737 --> 00:54:54,581
You look like someone I know.

1428
00:54:54,581 --> 00:54:57,719
No... I don't think we've met before...

1429
00:54:58,492 --> 00:54:59,988
You were just sitting here...

1430
00:54:59,988 --> 00:55:03,916
You've been to my place before, haven't you?
With PD Ji's letter.

1431
00:55:03,916 --> 00:55:05,235
Yes.

1432
00:55:05,235 --> 00:55:07,593
And you cried out on the street.

1433
00:55:09,168 --> 00:55:13,293
Don't walk around crying when it's cold.

1434
00:55:13,293 --> 00:55:15,070
Your face will freeze.

1435
00:55:16,214 --> 00:55:18,035
It was...

1436
00:55:18,035 --> 00:55:19,811
nice meeting you.

1437
00:55:24,813 --> 00:55:28,628
[The Grim Reaper hopes she'll forget
their painful past and be happy]

1438
00:55:28,628 --> 00:55:29,653
It was...

1439
00:55:29,653 --> 00:55:31,511
[Even that pain was precious,
but Sunny still had to walk away]

1440
00:55:31,511 --> 00:55:34,181
nice meeting you too...

1441
00:55:34,181 --> 00:55:36,237
Mr. Kim Woo Bin.

1442
00:55:37,785 --> 00:55:39,726
- That's why neither of us could say our lines.
- That's right.

1443
00:55:39,726 --> 00:55:43,820
- Back then, we were all really emotional.
- I guess we were.

1444
00:55:43,820 --> 00:55:45,913
- We were completely immersed in it.
- That's right.

1445
00:55:45,913 --> 00:55:48,372
I was really sad back then too.

1446
00:55:48,372 --> 00:55:50,631
When the Grim Reaper watched me

1447
00:55:50,631 --> 00:55:54,372
- after I died at the crosswalk...
- Oh, right.

1448
00:55:54,372 --> 00:55:55,857
- Right.
- Yeah, that was heartbreaking too.

1449
00:55:55,857 --> 00:55:56,883
That moment really...

1450
00:55:56,883 --> 00:55:57,991
- Oh, right.
- Yeah, that one is sad too.

1451
00:55:57,991 --> 00:56:00,018
- Remember?
- Yeah, I remember.

1452
00:56:00,018 --> 00:56:01,043
Mister!

1453
00:56:01,043 --> 00:56:06,915
[S# The Grim Reaper guides Eun Tak
after her death]

1454
00:56:11,602 --> 00:56:16,101
[Eun Tak could not escape her fate and died]

1455
00:56:16,101 --> 00:56:20,933
[They once again face a farewell
with no promise of reunion]

1456
00:56:20,933 --> 00:56:27,013
Born in the Year of the Warrior,
Gyeongsin Month, Gyehae Day.

1457
00:56:27,013 --> 00:56:28,758
Age 29.

1458
00:56:30,139 --> 00:56:31,932
Ji Eun Tak.

1459
00:56:33,692 --> 00:56:35,392
That's you...

1460
00:56:36,990 --> 00:56:38,690
isn't it?

1461
00:56:44,973 --> 00:56:46,673
I was...

1462
00:56:47,911 --> 00:56:51,081
so scared, Mister.

1463
00:56:53,455 --> 00:56:56,698
Before filming that scene...
the two of us just met like this,

1464
00:56:56,698 --> 00:56:57,723
and we were like...

1465
00:56:57,723 --> 00:56:59,091
We met... That's right.

1466
00:56:59,091 --> 00:57:00,512
- We met, and we both broke down.
- We were just like this.

1467
00:57:00,512 --> 00:57:01,711
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1468
00:57:01,711 --> 00:57:04,025
The moment I said, "Oh, you're here," and...

1469
00:57:05,753 --> 00:57:08,445
And we just started crying. We cried so much.

1470
00:57:08,445 --> 00:57:11,671
- That surprised me.
- There are so many heartbreaking scenes.

1471
00:57:11,671 --> 00:57:13,214
Two questions left? Only two now?

1472
00:57:13,214 --> 00:57:14,765
That's right, there are two questions left.

1473
00:57:14,765 --> 00:57:17,084
[Jumps up]
- I can't sit still. - You can't stay seated?

1474
00:57:17,084 --> 00:57:19,522
[Smack!]
Sir, sir!

1475
00:57:19,522 --> 00:57:20,997
[The Goblin can't wait for the next question]
Alright.

1476
00:57:20,997 --> 00:57:23,644
[Only two questions remain]
- There are only two questions left. - Yeah.

1477
00:57:23,644 --> 00:57:26,944
[Goblin & Go Eun tied for 1st with 10 points]
Goblin and Go Eun are tied with 10 points.

1478
00:57:26,944 --> 00:57:28,064
- Really?
- Yeah.

1479
00:57:28,064 --> 00:57:29,728
[I can't believe they caught up...]
The Grim Reaper actually has 9 points

1480
00:57:29,728 --> 00:57:31,579
- because I miscounted one point earlier.
- Oh, okay.

1481
00:57:31,579 --> 00:57:32,917
[9 pts / 7 pts / 7 pts / 6.5 pts]
- You're neck and neck. - It's a close match.

1482
00:57:32,917 --> 00:57:35,619
- Everyone else has 7 points.
- Okay.

1483
00:57:35,619 --> 00:57:37,691
What should we do?
Should this one be worth 3 points?

1484
00:57:37,691 --> 00:57:39,123
- Yes!
- No?

1485
00:57:39,123 --> 00:57:40,212
[Shakes head]
- How many questions are left? - This one...

1486
00:57:40,212 --> 00:57:42,115
- Two questions left.
- That feels a bit...

1487
00:57:42,115 --> 00:57:44,908
- Yeah.
- Three points feels a bit too much, MC.

1488
00:57:44,908 --> 00:57:46,533
- Alright then.
- I'd understand two points, but...

1489
00:57:46,533 --> 00:57:49,576
I'm happy with whatever you decide.

1490
00:57:49,576 --> 00:57:50,747
[Cute strategy]

1491
00:57:50,747 --> 00:57:52,863
- I think we should just go with...
- Seriously...

1492
00:57:52,863 --> 00:57:54,750
- 3 points for this question.
- Understood!

1493
00:57:54,750 --> 00:57:56,759
- If it's hard, let's make it 3 points.
- We'll do that!

1494
00:57:56,759 --> 00:57:58,848
- It's the final episode.
- If it's hard, let's make it 3 points.

1495
00:57:58,848 --> 00:58:00,033
[Jumps up]

1496
00:58:00,033 --> 00:58:02,746
Can you see better if you stand up?
Remember? Shall we go together?

1497
00:58:02,746 --> 00:58:05,732
[Recommending the kneeling strategy]
I think I can see better when I'm kneeling.

1498
00:58:05,732 --> 00:58:08,314
[Q. What was Kim Shin's confession to Eun Tak?]
This is Kim Shin's confession scene

1499
00:58:08,314 --> 00:58:10,848
[In deep concentration]
- to Eun Tak, 9 years later. - Alright.

1500
00:58:10,848 --> 00:58:13,123
I think I know this!

1501
00:58:13,123 --> 00:58:15,107
- Oh, I think I'll remember this one.
- Yeah?

1502
00:58:15,107 --> 00:58:16,791
Yeah, it's such an amazing scene.

1503
00:58:16,791 --> 00:58:19,659
[S# Kim Shin's confession after 9 years]
Wow... this is amazing. I'm so happy.

1504
00:58:19,659 --> 00:58:21,050
It feels unreal.

1505
00:58:21,050 --> 00:58:22,846
- The line here is really long though.
- When you were summoned on the first snow,

1506
00:58:22,846 --> 00:58:24,428
That's right.

1507
00:58:24,428 --> 00:58:29,555
was that...
what Kim Shin the warrior looked like?

1508
00:58:29,555 --> 00:58:30,704
- Yeah.
- Look at them.

1509
00:58:30,704 --> 00:58:33,163
[Acting along silently]
Oh, I see.

1510
00:58:33,163 --> 00:58:34,887
I've always wondered.

1511
00:58:34,887 --> 00:58:39,093
- Did I look strange?
- No, you looked amazing. A man from Goryeo.

1512
00:58:41,545 --> 00:58:44,118
Yeah, so that's why I'm saying this...

1513
00:58:45,370 --> 00:58:48,736
I'm saying this because today feels just right.

1514
00:58:51,242 --> 00:58:54,329
I'm saying this because you keep dazzling me.

1515
00:58:56,628 --> 00:59:01,108
I'm saying this because every one of
my first loves was you.

1516
00:59:02,282 --> 00:59:04,749
Then, on another day
when everything feels just right...

1517
00:59:06,166 --> 00:59:08,406
Uh, Go Eun!

1518
00:59:08,406 --> 00:59:11,635
Uh, Go Eun! Go Eun, Go Eun!

1519
00:59:11,635 --> 00:59:12,975
- Go Eun!
- Wow! Wow!

1520
00:59:12,975 --> 00:59:15,496
- Go Eun!
- You've got a great memory.

1521
00:59:15,496 --> 00:59:18,740
- Go Eun!
- "With this man from Goryeo...

1522
00:59:19,565 --> 00:59:22,956
could you marry me?"

1523
00:59:22,956 --> 00:59:25,118
- Goblin! Goblin!
- The meaning is right, but...

1524
00:59:25,118 --> 00:59:26,647
- Goblin, Goblin!
- Goblin!

1525
00:59:26,647 --> 00:59:29,129
"Will you be this Goryeo man's bride?"

1526
00:59:29,129 --> 00:59:30,560
- Oh, correct!
- Yes!

1527
00:59:30,560 --> 00:59:32,309
- Wow! Wow!
- Yes!

1528
00:59:32,309 --> 00:59:33,468
Isn't that worth three points?

1529
00:59:33,468 --> 00:59:34,955
- Right.
- It's three points!

1530
00:59:34,955 --> 00:59:36,937
[Goblin gets carried away]
- It's three points! - Wow!

1531
00:59:36,937 --> 00:59:39,209
[Three points]
- It's three points! - Wow!

1532
00:59:39,209 --> 00:59:41,842
[Goblin takes the sole lead with 13 points]
It's, "Will you be this Goryeo man's bride?"

1533
00:59:41,842 --> 00:59:43,073
[I had half of it right]

1534
00:59:43,073 --> 00:59:44,577
- Right.
- You were almost right...

1535
00:59:44,577 --> 00:59:48,061
- That was great. Ah, everything was perfect!
- Oh, right.

1536
00:59:48,061 --> 00:59:50,650
[A satisfied Goryeo man...]
Everything was perfect.

1537
00:59:50,650 --> 00:59:51,898
[And a frustrated bride]

1538
00:59:51,898 --> 00:59:54,268
"Will you be this Goryeo man's bride?"

1539
00:59:54,268 --> 00:59:55,305
[Answer revealed]

1540
00:59:55,305 --> 00:59:58,155
Then, on another day
when everything feels just right...

1541
00:59:58,155 --> 01:00:01,102
will you be this Goryeo man's bride?

1542
01:00:04,822 --> 01:00:07,257
Kyung Hye, why didn't you get it?

1543
01:00:07,257 --> 01:00:10,348
[Too absorbed in the scene to answer]
- I was just completely absorbed in it. - Oh.

1544
01:00:10,348 --> 01:00:11,523
- When the two of them were on screen together,
- You were too busy watching

1545
01:00:11,523 --> 01:00:14,131
- I got completely drawn in, yeah.
- and taking it all in.

1546
01:00:18,339 --> 01:00:20,458
I'm reminded again how good the OST is.

1547
01:00:20,458 --> 01:00:22,322
[Another unforgettable OST]

1548
01:00:22,322 --> 01:00:24,898
Wow, your gaze during that line was so intense.

1549
01:00:24,898 --> 01:00:28,708
But honestly... that wasn't
an easy line to deliver.

1550
01:00:28,708 --> 01:00:32,089
- Oh, really?
- Yeah, scenes like this are hard for me.

1551
01:00:32,089 --> 01:00:33,205
Because they're kind of cheesy?

1552
01:00:33,205 --> 01:00:35,238
- Yeah.
- Sure, that makes sense.

1553
01:00:35,238 --> 01:00:37,528
Then let's see you reenact it!

1554
01:00:38,389 --> 01:00:41,466
[He shouldn't have given them the idea]

1555
01:00:41,466 --> 01:00:44,684
Well, I'll just do it while looking at Eun Tak.

1556
01:00:44,684 --> 01:00:46,305
- We just wanted to see you say it
- I don't know.

1557
01:00:46,305 --> 01:00:48,790
- to Eun Tak one more time.
- Yeah.

1558
01:00:54,472 --> 01:00:57,442
Will you be this Goryeo man's bride?

1559
01:01:00,278 --> 01:01:03,600
Didn't you just say "Goryeo" funny?

1560
01:01:03,600 --> 01:01:05,171
[Blaming a stuffy nose,
the Goblin almost lost his "Goryeo"]

1561
01:01:05,171 --> 01:01:07,240
No, he was just...
his nose was stuffed, that's why!

1562
01:01:07,240 --> 01:01:08,274
I did my best.

1563
01:01:08,274 --> 01:01:09,666
- He did do it.
- He did.

1564
01:01:09,666 --> 01:01:12,622
Right, thank you so much
for actually doing that.

1565
01:01:12,622 --> 01:01:14,377
You earned it. The points count.

1566
01:01:14,377 --> 01:01:18,007
- It's just because my nose is stuffed.
- You're taking this game way too seriously.

1567
01:01:18,007 --> 01:01:19,843
[Seriously... maybe too seriously]
He really is.

1568
01:01:19,843 --> 01:01:21,424
Alright, this is the final question.

1569
01:01:21,424 --> 01:01:22,592
- The last question.
- But...

1570
01:01:22,592 --> 01:01:24,790
- Finally, the last question!
- we need a comeback twist now, don't we?

1571
01:01:24,790 --> 01:01:26,778
Whoever gets this right...

1572
01:01:26,778 --> 01:01:27,802
earns five points!

1573
01:01:27,802 --> 01:01:29,800
- Wow!
- Wow!

1574
01:01:29,800 --> 01:01:32,107
[Trouble strikes soon]

1575
01:01:32,107 --> 01:01:34,053
[Motivation through the roof]
Five points? Really?

1576
01:01:34,053 --> 01:01:36,156
Anyone can still make a comeback!

1577
01:01:36,156 --> 01:01:37,613
- Anyone can do it, it's worth five points!
- Yeah.

1578
01:01:37,613 --> 01:01:39,697
[A full 5 points, eyes locked
on a last-minute comeback]

1579
01:01:39,697 --> 01:01:42,812
I've got to get this one. This is serious.

1580
01:01:42,812 --> 01:01:44,562
- Here's the final question.
- Alright.

1581
01:01:44,562 --> 01:01:47,737
[Q. Kim Shin's words to reincarnated Eun Tak?]
Kim Shin reunites with reincarnated Eun Tak.

1582
01:01:47,737 --> 01:01:50,413
[He jumps up again]
It's from Episode 16. Let's watch.

1583
01:01:51,350 --> 01:01:55,879
[S# Kim Shin reunites
with the reincarnated Eun Tak]

1584
01:02:01,995 --> 01:02:03,822
Found you.

1585
01:02:07,597 --> 01:02:09,440
Mister.

1586
01:02:10,244 --> 01:02:12,467
You know who I am, don't you?

1587
01:02:22,779 --> 01:02:27,060
[An iconic line
from the final episode of Goblin]

1588
01:02:27,060 --> 01:02:29,412
- Me! Go Eun!
- Goblin! Goblin... ah...

1589
01:02:29,412 --> 01:02:31,521
[Just by a split second]
- Me! Go Eun! - Goblin! Goblin... ah...

1590
01:02:31,521 --> 01:02:34,037
Ow! I pulled my hip! I pulled my hip!

1591
01:02:34,037 --> 01:02:37,379
[The chance goes to Go Eun]
- Me! Go Eun! - Goblin! Goblin... ah...

1592
01:02:37,379 --> 01:02:41,151
[Will Go Eun get it in one try?]

1593
01:02:41,151 --> 01:02:44,805
"My first and my last... bride."

1594
01:02:44,805 --> 01:02:45,939
"My first

1595
01:02:45,939 --> 01:02:48,777
[Hesitating]
and my last..."

1596
01:02:48,777 --> 01:02:51,953
[The answer hyenas seize the opportunity]
"My first and my last..."

1597
01:02:52,548 --> 01:02:54,631
- Goblin! Goblin!
- Kyung Hye!

1598
01:02:54,631 --> 01:02:59,052
- "My first and my last... Goblin's bride."
- Correct!

1599
01:02:59,052 --> 01:03:00,687
[Congratulations!]

1600
01:03:00,687 --> 01:03:03,042
Ah, thank you!

1601
01:03:03,042 --> 01:03:04,492
[Go Eun recalls memories from
every lifetime to take first place]

1602
01:03:04,492 --> 01:03:06,232
Thank you!

1603
01:03:07,092 --> 01:03:08,903
[Disappointed Goblin]

1604
01:03:08,903 --> 01:03:11,337
If I'd just been a little faster,
I would've won.

1605
01:03:12,052 --> 01:03:13,539
Ah... there goes the beef.

1606
01:03:13,539 --> 01:03:16,216
[Still not over it]

1607
01:03:16,216 --> 01:03:17,148
[Answer revealed]

1608
01:03:17,148 --> 01:03:19,514
You know who I am, don't you?

1609
01:03:19,514 --> 01:03:21,591
My first and my last...

1610
01:03:23,248 --> 01:03:25,179
Goblin's bride.

1611
01:03:30,373 --> 01:03:33,274
[A touching happy ending,
even after all this time]

1612
01:03:33,274 --> 01:03:35,676
Ah... it's so sad.

1613
01:03:35,676 --> 01:03:37,401
- The funny thing is...
- Ah, it's so sad.

1614
01:03:37,401 --> 01:03:39,638
- We filmed this in advance.
- Yeah, you did.

1615
01:03:39,638 --> 01:03:40,882
Yeah, because you had to

1616
01:03:40,882 --> 01:03:43,046
- shoot it all while we were in Canada.
- You guys filmed it in Canada.

1617
01:03:43,046 --> 01:03:44,690
- That was early in the shoot, too.
- Like, really early.

1618
01:03:44,690 --> 01:03:47,392
- They shot the ending right at the start.
- We filmed the ending right at the beginning.

1619
01:03:47,392 --> 01:03:50,939
We went to Canada
before the full script was finished,

1620
01:03:50,939 --> 01:03:54,389
so Writer Eun Sook summarized the overall story

1621
01:03:54,389 --> 01:03:57,838
on an A4 sheet and told us,

1622
01:03:57,838 --> 01:04:00,484
[A story summary was provided for the actors]
"This is how the ending will go."

1623
01:04:00,484 --> 01:04:03,884
Apparently, she lost her memory...

1624
01:04:03,884 --> 01:04:05,881
and then she regained it.

1625
01:04:05,881 --> 01:04:08,234
[Emotional scenes filmed from a summary]
And then...

1626
01:04:09,232 --> 01:04:13,553
[The moment the maple leaf lands in her hand]

1627
01:04:13,553 --> 01:04:16,292
[Nine years of memories come flooding back]

1628
01:04:16,292 --> 01:04:19,120
After I said, "I miss you."

1629
01:04:24,628 --> 01:04:27,445
I miss you.

1630
01:04:28,073 --> 01:04:30,712
[In tears, she searches for Kim Shin]
I said I miss you!

1631
01:04:31,364 --> 01:04:33,756
Where are you?

1632
01:04:35,181 --> 01:04:37,736
I miss you!

1633
01:04:38,689 --> 01:04:45,412
[At last, the two are reunited]

1634
01:04:48,199 --> 01:04:54,138
[All of these scenes were filmed
at the very beginning]

1635
01:04:54,138 --> 01:04:55,956
Those emotional scenes...

1636
01:04:55,956 --> 01:04:57,659
- That's incredible.
- Looking back, it really wasn't easy.

1637
01:04:57,659 --> 01:04:58,832
It's really hard to pull off.

1638
01:04:58,832 --> 01:05:00,396
- It's really difficult.
- Yeah, it really was difficult.

1639
01:05:00,396 --> 01:05:02,981
You two are both such great actors.

1640
01:05:02,981 --> 01:05:04,240
- How did you even do that?
- We did a great job.

1641
01:05:04,240 --> 01:05:05,676
- You really did.
- You did a great job.

1642
01:05:05,676 --> 01:05:07,460
- Thank you, thank you.
- We did a great job.

1643
01:05:07,460 --> 01:05:09,906
[A legendary drama born from perfect chemistry]
- We did a great job! - You too.

1644
01:05:09,906 --> 01:05:11,844
- Wow...
- First place!

1645
01:05:11,844 --> 01:05:14,929
[No. 1 in acting and now in the quiz, too]
So today's winner is... Go Eun!

1646
01:05:14,929 --> 01:05:16,507
- Thank you.
- Congratulations!

1647
01:05:16,507 --> 01:05:18,267
You'll be taking home premium hanwoo.

1648
01:05:18,267 --> 01:05:20,600
- Wow!
- First place.

1649
01:05:20,600 --> 01:05:21,798
Wow!

1650
01:05:21,798 --> 01:05:23,165
It's real hanwoo.

1651
01:05:23,165 --> 01:05:25,163
[A chunk of beef worthy of Eun Tak]
- Wow... - Wow.

1652
01:05:25,163 --> 01:05:26,964
- Look at that marbling.
- Second prize is

1653
01:05:26,964 --> 01:05:29,682
maple syrup brought all the way from Canada.

1654
01:05:29,682 --> 01:05:31,774
- Congratulations.
- Maple syrup is so good.

1655
01:05:31,774 --> 01:05:33,157
Wow...

1656
01:05:33,157 --> 01:05:37,099
[Go Eun shares her prize with everyone]
I'll give you two packs each.

1657
01:05:37,099 --> 01:05:38,600
No, no.

1658
01:05:38,600 --> 01:05:42,120
No, I wasn't even offering it
to you, Dong Wook.

1659
01:05:42,120 --> 01:05:44,469
[Counting chickens before they hatch]

1660
01:05:44,469 --> 01:05:46,843
- You can have this one.
- I'd be happy to have it.

1661
01:05:46,843 --> 01:05:48,663
[The Goblin family even shares
a whole slab of beef]

1662
01:05:48,663 --> 01:05:50,362
Thank you, Go Eun. I'll enjoy it.

1663
01:05:50,362 --> 01:05:53,593
[The Goblin quiz ends on a heartwarming note]
- Thank you. I'll enjoy it. - Yeah.

1664
01:05:53,593 --> 01:05:55,412
[After the games ended,]

1665
01:05:55,412 --> 01:05:59,491
[another surprise
arrives for the Goblin family]

1666
01:05:59,491 --> 01:06:03,835
Those who couldn't make it today
sent video letters

1667
01:06:03,835 --> 01:06:06,461
- with their heartfelt messages.
- Oh, really?

1668
01:06:06,461 --> 01:06:08,097
Wow, this...

1669
01:06:08,097 --> 01:06:09,927
[Who could it be?]
No way!

1670
01:06:09,927 --> 01:06:10,968
That's amazing.

1671
01:06:10,968 --> 01:06:14,878
[Who sent this surprise message?]

1672
01:06:14,878 --> 01:06:16,959
Uncle!

1673
01:06:16,959 --> 01:06:18,434
[From the family that has served
the Goblin for generations]

1674
01:06:18,434 --> 01:06:20,009
Uncle!

1675
01:06:20,009 --> 01:06:21,039
No rain.

1676
01:06:21,039 --> 01:06:22,552
[The lovable third-generation chaebol]
If you're a chaebol, naturally...

1677
01:06:22,552 --> 01:06:26,222
you should drive a sedan to school
and make everyone notice you.

1678
01:06:26,222 --> 01:06:28,635
I don't know. If I were reincarnated,
I'd be around that age.

1679
01:06:28,635 --> 01:06:31,409
Court eunuch! Your Majesty's eunuch!

1680
01:06:31,409 --> 01:06:34,178
[Yook Sung Jae as Yoo Deok Hwa]

1681
01:06:34,178 --> 01:06:36,807
[The Goblin family's youngest, Deok Hwa]
Right, Deok Hwa.

1682
01:06:36,807 --> 01:06:38,905
[Nice to see him]

1683
01:06:38,905 --> 01:06:41,029
Hello, everyone.

1684
01:06:41,029 --> 01:06:43,829
I'm Yook Sung Jae,
who played Yoo Deok Hwa in Guardian.

1685
01:06:43,829 --> 01:06:44,998
[Hello, Sung Jae]
- Wow! - Hi!

1686
01:06:44,998 --> 01:06:47,097
Hi, Deok Hwa!

1687
01:06:47,097 --> 01:06:49,380
Oh, it's been such a long time.

1688
01:06:49,380 --> 01:06:52,892
Gong Yoo, Dong Wook, Go Eun, In Na...

1689
01:06:52,892 --> 01:06:54,442
I still have a lot to learn...

1690
01:06:54,442 --> 01:06:58,699
but back then, I was a complete
rookie and so nervous.

1691
01:06:58,699 --> 01:07:01,136
I was a clueless fool. A total fool.

1692
01:07:01,136 --> 01:07:03,329
[So cute]
But that Deok Hwa...

1693
01:07:03,329 --> 01:07:06,385
was guided so well, and I learned
so much from all of you.

1694
01:07:06,385 --> 01:07:08,801
I think I've grown a lot because of it.

1695
01:07:08,801 --> 01:07:10,848
Yeah, you guys really adored him.

1696
01:07:10,848 --> 01:07:12,659
[Sung Jae was dearly loved by the older cast]

1697
01:07:12,659 --> 01:07:14,302
Oh... the best scene?

1698
01:07:14,302 --> 01:07:16,990
Every scene was unforgettable,
but personally...

1699
01:07:16,990 --> 01:07:20,569
"God merely asks the question.
Destiny is the question I ask.

1700
01:07:20,569 --> 01:07:22,255
You must find the answer."

1701
01:07:22,255 --> 01:07:24,544
[A word from "God," speaking through Deok Hwa]
God merely asks the question.

1702
01:07:24,544 --> 01:07:26,485
Destiny is the question I ask.

1703
01:07:26,485 --> 01:07:29,277
You must find the answer.

1704
01:07:30,118 --> 01:07:32,455
And even saying goodbye to this boy...

1705
01:07:33,793 --> 01:07:35,697
it is for you to decide.

1706
01:07:41,408 --> 01:07:44,185
Yes, ten years still doesn't feel real to me.

1707
01:07:44,185 --> 01:07:47,513
For the past ten years,
almost everyone I've met has told me

1708
01:07:47,513 --> 01:07:48,852
they loved Guardian.

1709
01:07:48,852 --> 01:07:51,458
- They said they're still watching the reruns.
- Me too.

1710
01:07:51,458 --> 01:07:54,669
Everyone worked so hard and who knows?

1711
01:07:54,669 --> 01:07:57,483
[Hopes for Goblin Season 2 are alive]
Maybe Goblin will return for Season 2.

1712
01:07:57,483 --> 01:07:59,105
Maybe not?

1713
01:07:59,105 --> 01:08:00,746
I'll be waiting.

1714
01:08:00,746 --> 01:08:03,128
I wish you all good health and happiness.

1715
01:08:03,128 --> 01:08:05,932
I, Yook Sung Jae, who played Yoo Deok Hwa,
will always be cheering you on.

1716
01:08:05,932 --> 01:08:07,116
Thank you!

1717
01:08:07,116 --> 01:08:09,668
[Sung Jae's heartfelt message]
Thank you!

1718
01:08:09,668 --> 01:08:12,608
- It's so nice to see him, even like this.
- I know.

1719
01:08:12,608 --> 01:08:15,246
Oh, it's Senior Jo Woo Jin!

1720
01:08:17,371 --> 01:08:18,720
[Jo Woo Jin as Secretary Kim]
Yes.

1721
01:08:18,720 --> 01:08:19,744
- Yes.
- Yes.

1722
01:08:19,744 --> 01:08:22,353
[Secretary Kim's signature line]
Yes.

1723
01:08:22,353 --> 01:08:26,144
[His cute dance made him an idol secretary]
<i>♪ Why are you shaking my heart? ♪</i>

1724
01:08:26,144 --> 01:08:30,618
[The Goblin family's problem-solver]
The one with the Chairman's will...

1725
01:08:30,618 --> 01:08:33,469
Hello, Goblin family.

1726
01:08:33,469 --> 01:08:35,312
I'm Kim Byung Chul.

1727
01:08:36,872 --> 01:08:37,839
I'm Kim Byung Chul.

1728
01:08:37,839 --> 01:08:40,580
[The doppelgänger appears]

1729
01:08:40,580 --> 01:08:42,585
Yes, hello, I'm Jo Woo Jin.

1730
01:08:42,585 --> 01:08:45,985
[The two who were famous for looking alike]

1731
01:08:45,985 --> 01:08:49,489
We're celebrating Guardian's 10th anniversary,

1732
01:08:49,489 --> 01:08:51,892
yet it's still loved by so many people.

1733
01:08:51,892 --> 01:08:54,586
To me, Guardian is still ongoing,

1734
01:08:54,586 --> 01:08:57,147
rather than just a drama from the past.

1735
01:08:57,147 --> 01:09:01,168
I truly believe Guardian will live on forever.

1736
01:09:01,168 --> 01:09:02,608
I'll see you again for the 20th anniversary.

1737
01:09:02,608 --> 01:09:04,768
- Wow!
- Thank you, and stay strong!

1738
01:09:04,768 --> 01:09:07,565
[See you at the 20th anniversary!]

1739
01:09:07,565 --> 01:09:10,592
- I told you, I don't have the bankbook!
- It must be Yeom Hye Ran.

1740
01:09:10,592 --> 01:09:11,741
- I know.
- Wow!

1741
01:09:11,741 --> 01:09:15,388
I told you I don't have the bankbook!
How many times do I have to say it?

1742
01:09:15,388 --> 01:09:17,353
[Coveted Eun Tak's inheritance]
Where's your mother's insurance money?

1743
01:09:17,353 --> 01:09:20,255
Stop talking and bring it here
if you don't want to get hit!

1744
01:09:20,255 --> 01:09:22,903
Eun Tak, did you make lots of good food?

1745
01:09:22,903 --> 01:09:26,863
Otherwise, you know what I'll do, right?
I'll throw the bowl at you!

1746
01:09:26,863 --> 01:09:31,320
Hello, I'm Yeom Hye Ran, who played
Eun Tak's aunt. It's great to see you.

1747
01:09:33,623 --> 01:09:36,615
There were so many
unforgettable scenes and lines, too.

1748
01:09:36,615 --> 01:09:39,108
The one that stayed with me most was

1749
01:09:39,108 --> 01:09:43,397
when Eun Tak was being harassed by loan sharks.

1750
01:09:44,310 --> 01:09:47,705
The streetlights went out one by one...

1751
01:09:47,705 --> 01:09:49,631
[Streetlights going out one by one]
from the distance.

1752
01:09:53,595 --> 01:09:56,300
That scene where the Grim Reaper
and the Goblin appeared...

1753
01:09:56,300 --> 01:09:58,533
I'll never forget it.

1754
01:09:59,596 --> 01:10:02,417
[A scene forever etched into viewers' hearts]

1755
01:10:02,417 --> 01:10:05,784
Wow, that was so cool.

1756
01:10:05,784 --> 01:10:09,010
Every day spent with Guardian was wonderful.

1757
01:10:09,010 --> 01:10:12,504
Long live the immortal Guardian!

1758
01:10:12,504 --> 01:10:14,537
Long live!

1759
01:10:14,537 --> 01:10:17,104
That was so nice. I loved the video messages.

1760
01:10:17,104 --> 01:10:19,900
- It's Kyung Ho!
- Oh!

1761
01:10:20,984 --> 01:10:22,855
I'll be joining you soon.

1762
01:10:22,855 --> 01:10:28,814
[Yoon Kyung Ho as loyal retainer Kim Woo Sik]

1763
01:10:28,814 --> 01:10:32,297
Hello, everyone. It's great to see you.
I'm actor Yoon Kyung Ho.

1764
01:10:32,297 --> 01:10:35,372
Over there right now...
my dear Gong Yoo and everyone else...

1765
01:10:35,372 --> 01:10:37,824
[Kyung Ho is one year younger than Gong Yoo]
I know the whole family is together.

1766
01:10:37,824 --> 01:10:39,963
I really wish I could've been there
with you all.

1767
01:10:39,963 --> 01:10:42,107
I miss you all so much.

1768
01:10:42,107 --> 01:10:44,022
Should I sit down for a moment?

1769
01:10:46,218 --> 01:10:48,187
Is this going to be a long story?

1770
01:10:48,187 --> 01:10:50,430
I was so nervous on my first day of filming,

1771
01:10:50,430 --> 01:10:53,341
so I delivered all my lines way too loudly.

1772
01:10:53,341 --> 01:10:55,203
Gong Yoo, who reassured me with his warm gaze,

1773
01:10:55,203 --> 01:11:00,522
said, "You don't have to do this.
Don't be nervous."

1774
01:11:00,522 --> 01:11:04,488
- Oh...
- I'll never forget that warm look in his eyes.

1775
01:11:04,488 --> 01:11:06,986
At our final wrap party, he told me,

1776
01:11:06,986 --> 01:11:11,283
"I think we'll continue to
see each other often, wherever we are."

1777
01:11:11,283 --> 01:11:14,747
Since he said those words...
ten years have already passed.

1778
01:11:15,599 --> 01:11:17,362
I miss you so much, Gong Yoo.

1779
01:11:17,362 --> 01:11:18,709
[Moving to another spot]

1780
01:11:18,709 --> 01:11:22,373
I wanted to keep this lighter
and more cheerful...

1781
01:11:22,373 --> 01:11:25,010
[A variety of shots for the video letters]

1782
01:11:25,010 --> 01:11:27,340
The camera angles are really diverse.

1783
01:11:27,340 --> 01:11:30,386
I feel like I must have saved a country
in my past life.

1784
01:11:30,386 --> 01:11:32,543
I think it received so much love.

1785
01:11:32,543 --> 01:11:35,568
In the future,
for its 20th and 30th anniversaries,

1786
01:11:35,568 --> 01:11:41,138
I hope it will be remembered
as a masterpiece loved for many years.

1787
01:11:41,950 --> 01:11:46,172
[The video message from Kyung Ho
that even Goblin missed all day]

1788
01:11:46,172 --> 01:11:49,263
Oh! It's Hae In.

1789
01:11:51,006 --> 01:11:53,085
- Oh.
- Oh!

1790
01:11:53,085 --> 01:11:56,581
[The senior who stole Eun Tak's heart]
- Oh, Hae In. - Oh! Hae In, too?

1791
01:11:56,581 --> 01:12:00,279
So many actors really appeared...

1792
01:12:00,279 --> 01:12:01,304
Ji Eun Tak?

1793
01:12:01,304 --> 01:12:03,997
[Jung Hae In as Tae Hee]

1794
01:12:03,997 --> 01:12:06,713
Oh, he's patting her!

1795
01:12:08,825 --> 01:12:11,438
Hello, everyone. I'm Jung Hae In.

1796
01:12:11,438 --> 01:12:16,096
First of all, congratulations
on the 10th anniversary of Guardian!

1797
01:12:16,096 --> 01:12:18,853
It was such a happy filming experience.

1798
01:12:18,853 --> 01:12:23,763
At the time of filming,
I was a rookie actor with little experience.

1799
01:12:23,763 --> 01:12:26,712
The senior actors took great care of me
and looked after me,

1800
01:12:26,712 --> 01:12:29,304
so it remains a happy memory.

1801
01:12:29,304 --> 01:12:31,312
There are actually so many memorable scenes.

1802
01:12:31,312 --> 01:12:32,784
Senior actor Gong Yoo's

1803
01:12:32,784 --> 01:12:36,006
"Because the day was good,
because the day wasn't good...

1804
01:12:36,006 --> 01:12:39,557
Because the day was just right.
Every day was good."

1805
01:12:39,557 --> 01:12:41,872
"Every moment I spent with you was dazzling."

1806
01:12:41,872 --> 01:12:47,178
These simple yet wonderful lines
stayed with me.

1807
01:12:47,178 --> 01:12:51,184
It was truly an honor and I'm grateful

1808
01:12:51,184 --> 01:12:54,368
to have been a part of Guardian.

1809
01:12:54,368 --> 01:12:55,392
Wow!

1810
01:12:55,392 --> 01:12:58,132
[Just heartwarming]

1811
01:12:58,929 --> 01:13:01,435
- Oh, my.
- Oh!

1812
01:13:02,929 --> 01:13:07,263
[Who was the surprise guest
who amazed everyone?]

1813
01:13:09,757 --> 01:13:12,779
[Kim Sung Kyum as Chairman Yoo Shin Woo]
It's been 20 years since I last saw you.

1814
01:13:12,779 --> 01:13:15,844
[Protecting the Goblin for a lifetime]
It's Gon Ma, My Lord.

1815
01:13:15,844 --> 01:13:19,225
[The respected elder
of the Yoo family who served him]

1816
01:13:22,403 --> 01:13:26,888
My Lord, it's been 10 years
since I last saw you.

1817
01:13:26,888 --> 01:13:31,308
My Lord, it's been 10 years
since I last saw you.

1818
01:13:31,308 --> 01:13:33,510
How have you been all this time?

1819
01:13:33,510 --> 01:13:39,864
You have always remained
as "My Lord" in my heart.

1820
01:13:40,636 --> 01:13:44,959
[Currently 86 years old]
Hello everyone, it's nice to see you.

1821
01:13:44,959 --> 01:13:48,819
Hello everyone, it's nice to see you.

1822
01:13:48,819 --> 01:13:54,775
[Seeing the Chairman again after a long time]

1823
01:13:55,953 --> 01:13:59,599
Whenever I think back to Guardian,

1824
01:13:59,599 --> 01:14:04,416
it feels like such a long time ago,
but it's already been 10 years.

1825
01:14:05,484 --> 01:14:06,558
Oh, it makes me tear up.

1826
01:14:06,558 --> 01:14:10,698
They say that even mountains
and rivers change after 10 years,

1827
01:14:10,698 --> 01:14:14,235
so many things must have changed.

1828
01:14:14,235 --> 01:14:17,765
But the people have stayed the same.

1829
01:14:18,882 --> 01:14:21,965
So much time has passed.

1830
01:14:21,965 --> 01:14:26,043
It feels like it was just yesterday.

1831
01:14:26,043 --> 01:14:32,004
Congratulations on the 10th anniversary
broadcast of Guardian.

1832
01:14:32,004 --> 01:14:37,618
Thinking that it will continue to be loved
for another 20 or 30 years

1833
01:14:37,618 --> 01:14:41,030
gives me strength.

1834
01:14:41,030 --> 01:14:43,805
I think it will be wonderful.

1835
01:14:45,061 --> 01:14:49,746
Even though it's been a long time
since I saw Gong Yoo,

1836
01:14:49,746 --> 01:14:52,212
it feels like I see him every day.

1837
01:14:55,521 --> 01:15:00,848
I feel a special closeness,
and I really like him.

1838
01:15:00,848 --> 01:15:04,027
I love you, My Lord.

1839
01:15:04,027 --> 01:15:07,138
I love you, My Lord.

1840
01:15:27,601 --> 01:15:31,912
I was really surprised because someone
I never expected appeared.

1841
01:15:33,349 --> 01:15:37,689
Well, it was great to see him
looking healthy in the video.

1842
01:15:37,689 --> 01:15:41,475
But I wasn't expecting it at all,

1843
01:15:41,475 --> 01:15:43,447
[Unexpected greeting from Kim Sung Kyum]
and then suddenly...

1844
01:15:43,447 --> 01:15:46,650
But it really got to me, like...

1845
01:15:46,650 --> 01:15:51,611
It made me think of my father too,
since he's around the same age.

1846
01:15:52,412 --> 01:15:54,216
It was so much fun acting together.

1847
01:15:54,216 --> 01:15:57,021
He treated me comfortably

1848
01:15:57,021 --> 01:16:00,336
[Remembering his kindness as a senior actor]
and was not authoritative at all.

1849
01:16:00,336 --> 01:16:02,489
He was very...

1850
01:16:06,574 --> 01:16:08,791
Why are you over there with her, Grandpa?

1851
01:16:08,791 --> 01:16:11,526
[In the hearts of the actors]
He is the grandson I mentioned.

1852
01:16:11,526 --> 01:16:14,987
[And in the hearts of the viewers...]
He will stay one floor below.

1853
01:16:14,987 --> 01:16:17,701
- I carried you.
- Ah, you're taking your jokes too far.

1854
01:16:17,701 --> 01:16:20,136
[Kim Sung Kyum's unforgettable performance
that will be remembered for a long time]

1855
01:16:20,136 --> 01:16:21,670
You're feeling nervous, aren't you?

1856
01:16:21,670 --> 01:16:25,711
It's the punishment
for saying goodbye so carefully.

1857
01:16:25,711 --> 01:16:27,605
I'll accept it gladly.

1858
01:16:29,009 --> 01:16:35,591
He had to leave the show early
because he wasn't feeling well.

1859
01:16:35,591 --> 01:16:37,512
They revised the script.

1860
01:16:37,512 --> 01:16:42,734
So I believe it was changed to the scene
where he played baduk with me.

1861
01:16:42,734 --> 01:16:46,057
[He left the show after the baduk scene]
He had to leave because of his health...

1862
01:16:47,761 --> 01:16:50,567
- But I'm glad he's healthy now.
- That's right.

1863
01:16:50,567 --> 01:16:57,127
But he treats you just like the Goblin
we all remember,

1864
01:16:57,880 --> 01:17:02,391
with the same feelings
we've always had, so that was...

1865
01:17:02,391 --> 01:17:06,085
- Yeah, my first thought was exactly that.
- Right, in the beginning...

1866
01:17:06,085 --> 01:17:08,250
- Even now, he still calls you "My Lord."
- That's right.

1867
01:17:08,250 --> 01:17:10,917
- That really moved me.
- That's right.

1868
01:17:10,917 --> 01:17:14,081
["My Lord" forever, even after ten years]
Exactly, that hit me so hard.

1869
01:17:14,081 --> 01:17:18,846
Maybe even after 20 or 30 years,

1870
01:17:18,846 --> 01:17:23,622
I think you are everyone's Goblin.

1871
01:17:26,653 --> 01:17:28,742
Why are you crying so much?

1872
01:17:28,742 --> 01:17:31,705
[Crying]

1873
01:17:31,705 --> 01:17:33,688
Why are you crying so much?

1874
01:17:33,688 --> 01:17:36,428
What do you want me to do?
How am I supposed to help?

1875
01:17:36,428 --> 01:17:38,357
- Bring me some tissues.
- Tissues?

1876
01:17:38,357 --> 01:17:40,368
Bring her quickly.

1877
01:17:40,368 --> 01:17:42,904
These are wet wipes.

1878
01:17:42,904 --> 01:17:45,849
[Doing everything she's asked]
- Give some to me and Go Eun too. - Yeah.

1879
01:17:46,600 --> 01:17:50,197
- So many amazing actors were part of this.
- Yeah, they're all...

1880
01:17:50,197 --> 01:17:53,086
It's truly an honor.

1881
01:17:53,717 --> 01:17:55,118
[Kim Min Jae as young King Wang Yeo]
Go as far away as you can,

1882
01:17:55,118 --> 01:17:57,690
and don't come back as much as possible.

1883
01:17:57,690 --> 01:17:59,318
[Kim So Hyun as young Kim Sun]
It is my destiny.

1884
01:17:59,318 --> 01:18:01,546
Go to His Majesty, General.

1885
01:18:02,132 --> 01:18:04,990
[Lee Kyoo Hyung as the shameless husband]
Where do you keep looking while talking?

1886
01:18:04,990 --> 01:18:07,050
[Kim Nam Hee as the overworked doctor]
Is the OR ready?

1887
01:18:07,050 --> 01:18:09,077
We don't have time. Hurry.

1888
01:18:09,077 --> 01:18:10,972
[Kim Hye Yoon as the separated wife's role]
I've grown old waiting for you,

1889
01:18:10,972 --> 01:18:12,840
so what's there to be pretty?

1890
01:18:12,840 --> 01:18:15,178
[Park Hee Von as Eun Tak's mother]
Please be here when I return.

1891
01:18:15,178 --> 01:18:18,246
[Hwang Seok Jeong as the ghost, fortune teller]
That guy is the Grim Reaper.

1892
01:18:18,246 --> 01:18:24,245
[Guardian brightened by many actors]

1893
01:18:24,245 --> 01:18:30,215
The drama Guardian gave me
a nickname because of my character,

1894
01:18:30,215 --> 01:18:32,935
and today's gathering was
very meaningful and happy.

1895
01:18:32,935 --> 01:18:36,277
- That is what I would like to say.
- Seriously... wow.

1896
01:18:36,277 --> 01:18:37,309
Thank you.

1897
01:18:37,309 --> 01:18:40,444
Ten years ago, every actor,

1898
01:18:40,444 --> 01:18:43,683
every staff member, and our entire team...

1899
01:18:43,683 --> 01:18:46,410
"We all did well.
Everyone did an incredible job."

1900
01:18:46,410 --> 01:18:49,382
It feels like the day we received an award,
so I'm very happy.

1901
01:18:49,382 --> 01:18:53,716
I was so happy and glad that
we could all see each other again.

1902
01:18:53,716 --> 01:18:55,292
If we get another chance,

1903
01:18:55,292 --> 01:18:58,559
I hope we can go on another trip
together someday. Thank you.

1904
01:18:58,559 --> 01:18:59,617
She's so cute.

1905
01:18:59,617 --> 01:19:03,076
So that we can meet again like this,

1906
01:19:03,076 --> 01:19:07,528
beautifully, 10 or 20 years from now,
let's all stay healthy.

1907
01:19:07,528 --> 01:19:09,704
- Let's stay healthy.
- Let's stay healthy.

1908
01:19:09,704 --> 01:19:11,518
- Thank you for inviting us.
- Health is the most important thing.

1909
01:19:11,518 --> 01:19:13,701
- The best!
- The best!

1910
01:19:13,701 --> 01:19:16,618
[Until we meet again, stay healthy and happy]
- Let's stay healthy. - Yeah!

1911
01:19:16,618 --> 01:19:18,079
- Please get home safely.
- Bye.

1912
01:19:18,079 --> 01:19:19,537
- Thank you.
- Bye.

1913
01:19:19,537 --> 01:19:21,386
- Bye.
- Bye-bye.

1914
01:19:21,386 --> 01:19:24,028
- Goodbye.
- Yeah!

1915
01:19:27,452 --> 01:19:29,152
Let's go inside.

1916
01:19:31,340 --> 01:19:35,191
- Ah, I'm hungry.
- I am kind of hungry, though.

1917
01:19:36,514 --> 01:19:38,180
What is this sprinkled on top?

1918
01:19:38,180 --> 01:19:40,248
[Late-night snack time before bed]
This is fried chicken,

1919
01:19:40,248 --> 01:19:42,181
and this one is dried pollack chicken.

1920
01:19:42,181 --> 01:19:43,647
You like dried pollack, right?

1921
01:19:43,647 --> 01:19:44,835
[The spiciness of Cheongyang peppers
and the savory taste of dried pollack]

1922
01:19:44,835 --> 01:19:46,771
Oh, so this is how they serve dried pollack.

1923
01:19:46,771 --> 01:19:48,883
Usually, you order dried pollack separately.

1924
01:19:48,883 --> 01:19:51,536
- But we don't need to order it separately.
- Right.

1925
01:19:51,536 --> 01:19:54,591
I guess we have some connection with chicken.

1926
01:19:54,591 --> 01:19:56,201
- The chicken shop owner
- You're right.

1927
01:19:56,201 --> 01:19:58,474
- and the chicken shop part-timer.
- You're right.

1928
01:19:58,474 --> 01:20:00,533
If you've had enough, please leave.

1929
01:20:00,533 --> 01:20:02,209
[They met at a chicken shop 10 years ago]
It's almost time for customers to come in.

1930
01:20:02,209 --> 01:20:03,909
- No!
- No!

1931
01:20:04,654 --> 01:20:07,924
- Can the youngest eat first?
- Go ahead, eat while it's hot.

1932
01:20:10,044 --> 01:20:12,455
The drumsticks, have the drumsticks.

1933
01:20:12,455 --> 01:20:15,250
- A little bit...
- You're right.

1934
01:20:15,250 --> 01:20:17,248
This is really delicious.

1935
01:20:17,248 --> 01:20:19,245
Since the original fried chicken is good,

1936
01:20:19,245 --> 01:20:21,464
[A solid classic fried chicken]
the other menu is good too.

1937
01:20:21,464 --> 01:20:23,203
Aren't you really proud of today?

1938
01:20:23,203 --> 01:20:24,312
[A fulfilling day from dawn to dusk]
- We... - Wow.

1939
01:20:24,312 --> 01:20:26,219
- all woke up at five.
- That's right.

1940
01:20:26,219 --> 01:20:27,326
The day was long.

1941
01:20:27,326 --> 01:20:28,492
- We did so much.
- Wow...

1942
01:20:28,492 --> 01:20:31,248
- we really did a lot.
- No, it was short.

1943
01:20:31,248 --> 01:20:34,536
No, my day isn't over yet.

1944
01:20:34,536 --> 01:20:37,038
Isn't over yet? That's right.

1945
01:20:37,038 --> 01:20:39,499
- Isn't this normally your bedtime, In Na?
- It's my bedtime...

1946
01:20:39,499 --> 01:20:41,114
It's my bedtime.

1947
01:20:41,114 --> 01:20:42,821
Go to sleep.

1948
01:20:44,291 --> 01:20:45,928
- Just sleep first.
- Alright, go to sleep now.

1949
01:20:45,928 --> 01:20:47,127
- This...
- Stand up.

1950
01:20:47,127 --> 01:20:48,825
- Clean up this chicken tomorrow.
- This is our home anyway.

1951
01:20:48,825 --> 01:20:50,322
- Our home is here.
- Clean this up tomorrow.

1952
01:20:50,322 --> 01:20:52,626
- You drink, Gong Yoo. I'll go to sleep.
- I'll just drink what's left.

1953
01:20:52,626 --> 01:20:53,693
- Gong Yoo...
- I'm leaving.

1954
01:20:53,693 --> 01:20:57,233
- Good night, Dong Wook. Sleep well.
- Good night.

1955
01:21:15,434 --> 01:21:18,709
I won't be able to see you again in this life.

1956
01:21:18,709 --> 01:21:21,137
[Their unfinished story from their past lives]

1957
01:21:21,844 --> 01:21:24,757
- Every moment was...
- It felt too short.

1958
01:21:24,757 --> 01:21:27,250
Time went by so quickly.

1959
01:21:29,755 --> 01:21:32,514
[Even before the fate of death]
Until death separates us...

1960
01:21:32,514 --> 01:21:36,556
[The Goblin couple who vowed their love]
Every word you say, whatever it may be...

1961
01:21:36,556 --> 01:21:38,318
Me too.

1962
01:21:41,836 --> 01:21:43,326
[With only a little time left,
they are filled with regret]

1963
01:21:43,326 --> 01:21:45,915
Yesterday feels like a dream.

1964
01:21:45,915 --> 01:21:46,930
Did you put on sunscreen?

1965
01:21:46,930 --> 01:21:48,285
- No, I didn't.
- Come here.

1966
01:21:48,285 --> 01:21:50,623
[Gong Yoo & Go Eun making
the most of their time together]

1967
01:21:50,623 --> 01:21:52,605
I want to live here.

1968
01:21:52,605 --> 01:21:54,484
No, you can't live here.

1969
01:21:55,180 --> 01:21:56,909
Oh, seriously...

1970
01:21:56,909 --> 01:21:58,125
[The final sprint to make memories]
What?

1971
01:21:58,125 --> 01:21:59,809
- Wow!
- Wow.

1972
01:21:59,809 --> 01:22:01,525
[The Goblin family's must-do list in this life]
What is this?

1973
01:22:01,525 --> 01:22:03,767
[Building family bonds with a 2-on-2 Yut game!]
What is this?

1974
01:22:03,767 --> 01:22:05,107
Please help me.

1975
01:22:05,107 --> 01:22:06,845
- Yut!
- Wow!

1976
01:22:06,845 --> 01:22:07,901
[Yay]
Wow...

1977
01:22:07,901 --> 01:22:09,502
[100% fully immersed]
- I'm genuinely annoyed. - Hey, don't worry.

1978
01:22:09,502 --> 01:22:11,304
[The Grim Reaper & the forgotten
member getting overly excited]

1979
01:22:11,304 --> 01:22:12,456
[Who will be the winner
amid the intense competition?]

1980
01:22:12,456 --> 01:22:13,731
This is driving me crazy.

1981
01:22:13,731 --> 01:22:16,188
[The Goblin family's must-do list in this life:
Devouring food!]

1982
01:22:16,188 --> 01:22:18,802
[The Goblin family's appetite explodes]

1983
01:22:18,802 --> 01:22:20,150
[The honest brow furrow]
Yum!

1984
01:22:20,150 --> 01:22:21,863
[In Na also takes a bite]

1985
01:22:21,863 --> 01:22:25,067
- Let's order three more of these.
- What did you say?

1986
01:22:25,067 --> 01:22:26,973
Dong Wook, this is so much fun.

1987
01:22:26,973 --> 01:22:28,185
[The Goblin family's must-do list in this life:
Riding bicycles]

1988
01:22:28,185 --> 01:22:29,354
Oh, seriously...

1989
01:22:29,354 --> 01:22:30,991
[Happiness]

1990
01:22:30,991 --> 01:22:32,584
[Must-do list in this life: Buying gifts]
How is it?

1991
01:22:32,584 --> 01:22:33,731
[I want to buy this]

1992
01:22:33,731 --> 01:22:36,081
[The Peach couple's flex shopping]
Get it. Do you take Apple Pay?

1993
01:22:36,081 --> 01:22:38,752
- Goblin, buy this for me.
- What else do you want me to buy?

1994
01:22:38,752 --> 01:22:39,766
[After the shopping spree]
Buy it, buy it.

1995
01:22:39,766 --> 01:22:42,433
[Must-do list: Taking memory photos]
Go Eun, where should I write your name?

1996
01:22:42,433 --> 01:22:44,552
[A firm stamp]
- Just write it here. - Here?

1997
01:22:44,552 --> 01:22:47,248
[The happiest one in the world]

1998
01:22:47,248 --> 01:22:49,767
[Go Eun also leaves a memory stamp for In Na!]

1999
01:22:49,767 --> 01:22:52,530
[Even a happy painting made
together by the four of them]

2000
01:22:52,530 --> 01:22:57,627
I think every moment was truly brilliant.

2001
01:22:59,373 --> 01:23:02,150
[And...]

2002
01:23:02,150 --> 01:23:03,191
[Ding dong]

2003
01:23:03,191 --> 01:23:05,697
- What is it?
- Is the doorbell ringing right now?

2004
01:23:05,697 --> 01:23:08,067
[A mysterious doorbell at the Goblin's house]
Is the doorbell really ringing?

2005
01:23:08,067 --> 01:23:09,365
[Ding dong]

2006
01:23:09,365 --> 01:23:10,390
[Grab]

2007
01:23:10,390 --> 01:23:12,860
The doorbell at our house
has never rung even once.

2008
01:23:12,860 --> 01:23:14,968
Huh?

2009
01:23:14,968 --> 01:23:17,467
[Who rang the Goblin family's doorbell
on their last day?]
